title: oatmeal pie (mock pecan)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for about one hour.

title: au gratin potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips or corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside. Sift flour and sugar into beaten egg yolks. Add milk, lemon juice, rind and melted butter. Fold in egg whites until smooth. Pour into a buttered 1-quart baking dish. Set in a shallow pan of water. Bake at 350° until firm and golden brown on top, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
These cookies do not rise or spread.
So spread as desired on greased cookie sheet.
Use large tablespoon and spread slightly.
Makes a very moist cookie.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer the remaining ingredients on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: calorie counter crepes
directions: Whisk together until well beaten.
Heat 1 teaspoon shortening in small Teflon frying pan until melted. Quickly spoon 3 tablespoons of crepe batter into pan, tipping pan slightly to even out batter.
Cook until edges begin to brown, then invert on paper towels.
Continue until all are cooked.
Makes 18.

title: ranch house stew
directions: Coat beef with flour and salt.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Add water and tomato sauce with onion.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add carrots and celery, simmer 1/2 hour or until vegetables are done and meat is tender.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes or peel.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly to open slices.
Sprinkle with salt and melted butter, then sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add Cheddar cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage ramen salad
directions: Shake the vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in a jar until sugar dissolves.
Brown the crushed noodles and sesame seeds in a skillet with a small amount of oil.
When they begin to brown, add the almonds and brown a bit more, watching almonds as they burn easily.
Cool this mixture.
Just before serving, combine all ingredients and toss well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt Cheddar cheese. Add sausage and Bisquick. Make into balls. Bake about 15 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add raw nuts. Cook, stirring constantly, to the hard crack stage.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, butter and soda.
Mix well and pour on buttered surface.
As it cools, stretch thinly.
Break in small pieces.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into serving-size pieces; pat dry and set aside. Over medium heat, saute garlic, onion and celery in oil, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add green pepper; cook another 2 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Increase heat to medium-high; brown chicken all sides, about 6 to 7 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have margarine and cream cheese at room temperature.
Cream well with sugar.
Add one egg at a time and mix well.
Sift flour and salt together; gradually add to mixture.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Bake in greased and flour-dusted Bundt pan or round tube cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: *Use 1 1/2 cups Monterey Jack and 1 1/2 cups Cheddar.

title: tortillas
directions: Stir dry ingredients and then cut in shortening.
Let rest for 10 to 15 minutes.
Shape dough into 7 or 8 egg size balls. Roll out thin.
Cook on hot griddle.
When done, stack together on plate.

title: pow wows
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain well; crumble.
Combine with other ingredients.
Spread on buns.
Top with a slice of cheese. Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Mix chicken, cheeses, onion, chilies and sour cream.
(It's easiest to do this with your hands.)
Put 2/3 cup of the mixture in the center of each tortilla and roll up.
Cook the rolled tortillas, seam side down first, in 1/2 to 1-inch of hot oil until tortillas are well browned on all sides.
Serve hot with salsa, sour cream or guacamole on the side.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil and drain excess fat.
Combine sauce and water. Pour over chicken, cover and simmer 40 minutes, or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Remove cover.
Simmer an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Skim excess fat from sauce and serve sauce over chicken.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour on top of melted butter.
Add fruit, including juice, on top of batter. Bake until crust is golden brown.
Good served hot with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: stir-fry asparagus
directions: Heat in skillet the salad oil and garlic, then add the celery, asparagus, onion and mushrooms.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Add soy sauce.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and taco mix.
Spread in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Layer remainder in order listed.
Makes 8 cups.
Serve with corn chips.

title: salad supreme
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
Let stand in refrigerator until thick.
Add pineapple to thickened jello.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package; add cream cheese and spread over jello.
Mix remaining ingredients well and cook until thick.
Let cool. Spread over cream mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press as crust in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Saute the celery, onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mix all ingredients well, reserving 1 cup of grated cheese.
Place chicken mixture in casserole and top with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Serves 25.

title: sushi salad
directions: Cook rice in a mixture of shoyu and 2 cups water.
Remove from heat and cool.
Rinse shrimp and drain thoroughly.
Reserve 1/2 cup of shrimp.
Combine remaining shrimp, carrots, peas, green onions and ginger in a large bowl.
Fluff rice with fork.
Fold in shrimp mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: spanish potato omelet
directions: Brown and crumble sausage; drain.
Cook potatoes, green pepper and onion in margarine (or if not too much grease from sausage, you can use the sausage fat) until tender.
Spoon vegetables into well-greased 9 x 13-inch (or next size larger) casserole dish. Arrange evenly and then spoon sausage evenly over vegetables. Combine eggs, salt and pepper; beat well.
Add salsa and mix well. Pour over vegetables and meat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until eggs are set.
Top with cheese slices; return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine orange rind, juice and egg.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool. Wrap and store overnight.

title: whole wheat brick alley bread
directions: In a large bowl combine flours, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine the 1 beaten egg, buttermilk and honey.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Turn dough out onto a greased baking sheet; pat with wet fingers to an 8-inch round (dough will be wet).
Brush with egg white.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins in 3 1/2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Crisco and sugar.
Stir and set aside to cool.
Add all dry ingredients to mixture and mix well.
Pour in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy no-bake cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Shape into small balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Enjoy!

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw out bread overnight in the refrigerator.
Cut into 12 pieces. Dip each piece into melted butter, then in Parmesan cheese.
Place in greased Bundt pan and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Combine 2 cups cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press mixture into bottom of greased baking pan.
Add drained broccoli and layer slices of Velveeta on top.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top and bake at 300° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix celery and mushroom soup and milk together in bowl.
Put rice in 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Pour mix of soup and milk over rice.
Put in pieces of chicken (as many as you can fit in pan).
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup on chicken.
Cover pan good with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven 2 hours at 350°.

title: tangy italian beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions; drain.
Toss bacon, onions and eggs with cooked beans.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to bean mixture.
Serve hot or chilled on fresh salad greens.

title: nancy's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth consistency is attained.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together; beat in eggs, one at a time and slowly mix in sour cream and flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternating sour cream and flour.
Last, mix in flavoring.
Grease pan and lightly flour a 15 x 4-inch cake pan and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Test by inserting toothpick.

title: bacon or ham quiche
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until smooth and set aside.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese, onion and mushrooms into a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour liquid ingredients over and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; mix in sugar and let stand overnight. Slice bananas and unpeeled apples.
Add to cranberry mixture along with the marshmallows.
Whip and sweeten cream and add to mixture. Chill.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix for streusel and sprinkle over top of pie filling.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Cover with rind and juice of lemons; add beaten egg yolks and boiling water.
Cook until just thick.
When cool, pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue and brown in oven at 425° for 5 minutes.

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Mix vinegar and soda; set aside.
Mix cocoa and coloring; set aside.
Cream sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add cocoa and coloring.
Add milk, flour and baking powder alternately.
Add vinegar and soda and beat again well.
Bake in 3 layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grits casserole
directions: In saucepan, bring water and salt to boil.
Slowly stir in grits.
Reduce heat and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove grits from heat and add a small amount of grits into eggs.
Return to saucepan, stir in sausage, 1 cup cheese, milk and oleo.
Stir until oleo melts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until starts to brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Add sour milk; blend in dry ingredients.
Bake at 365° for about 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a buttered long glass dish. Spread pineapple with the juice on top of the pie filling.
Next, spread dry cake mix, then add pecans on top.
Next, slice margarine on top; try to space margarine all over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash the avocado to a paste with fork.
Add lemon juice, onion, mayonnaise, Tabasco and salt (to taste).
Blend thoroughly and serve.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar and egg.
Add rhubarb, crumbs, salt, raisins and butter or butter substitute.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain 3 cans of beans.
Wash and chop onion and pepper.
Make a well blended marinade of salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and oil. Pour marinade over beans, pepper and onion.
Bean salad must marinate overnight before eating.

title: egg custard
directions: Butter around little cups or put in pie crust.
Scald milk (do not boil).
Add to eggs.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes. Shake to see if it is firm enough.
If longer cooking is needed reduce heat to 350°.

title: chicken with sherry sauce
directions: Saute onion and chicken pieces in margarine until golden brown. Arrange

in large baking dish. Blend mushrooms, tomato sauce, sauce mix and sherry. Pour over chicken pieces. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes in preheated 375° oven. Before serving, garnish with pepper strips. Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana icebox cake
directions: Spread graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bananas over crackers.
Prepare pudding according to directions and carefully spread over bananas.
Add layer of crackers on top. Refrigerate overnight or until firm.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together dry cake mix, salt, baking soda and oil until blended.
Add nuts if desired.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crust is brown around the edges.

title: green chili burrito casserole
directions: Put 2 cans of soup in saucepan; add 1 can water and can of green chilies.
Heat up.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add Ranch and refried beans.
Warm tortillas and make burritos.
Layer in cake (lasagna) pan.
Pour 1/2 sauce on top of first layer.
Make rest of burritos and place on top.
Pour rest of sauce on top. Top with cheese.
Heat oven to 375°.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in a very deep baking dish and place in a 350° oven. Make a batter of the sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Mix well.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Pour sliced peaches into batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jimmy's chix dish - el rancho chix
directions: Mix together Rotel, and both cans of soup and chili powder. In a 13 x 9 baking dish, layer tortillas, chicken, sauce, and cheese. Start over same order. with the last layer being tortillas and cheese. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Uncover the last 5 or 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. Use 1 to 2 teaspoons of mix per mug of boiling water.

title: lemon bread pudding with meringue
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar.
Pour in milk. Add bread, lemon rind and vanilla. Cook like a custard in hot oven for 1/2 hour.
Beat egg whites and lemon juice for meringue.

title: garden stir-fry #1
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken; stir until no longer pink.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until just tender-crisp.
Stir in rest of seasons.
Add the spaghetti; toss to mix.

title: peanut butter molasses cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: baked skinless chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken and pull off skin.
Lightly sprinkle salt, pepper and Season-All on chicken.
Place chicken and green pepper in roaster and bake for 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Add the can of cream of chicken soup and water to roaster and cover.
Turn heat down to low.
Bake about 10 minutes longer and test for doneness.

title: colonial peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press into buttered pan and refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: sparkling citrus holiday punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Add ice cubes and garnish (optional) before serving.
Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: leslie's chinese chews
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter; add noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to cool.
Eat!!

title: chocolate cake
directions: To the yolks of 8 eggs, add sugar.
Stir until consistency is thick and light in color.
Add juice and rind of orange, cocoa, wine and cake meal.
Mix well.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broiled dijon chicken breasts
directions: Heat broiler.
Line a broiler pan rack with foil for easy cleanup.
Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken, smooth side down, on lined rack.
Brush with half of mayonnaise mixture.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat source for 6 minutes. Turn breasts over and brush with remaining mayonnaise mixture. Broil 6 minutes longer or until chicken is cooked through and lightly browned.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° until done or when a toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll or spread cookie dough out on cookie sheet; bake as package directions state or until golden brown at edges. Let cool completely. Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together. Add sugar to taste. Spread over cooled cookie dough. Place sliced fruit on top of baked cookie dough (making your Fruit Pizza).

title: tuna cheesets
directions: Spread on buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Heat in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients and beat together 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange peaches over batter in pie plate.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Whip the cream cheese.
Add all other ingredients together. Add to cheese.

title: pickle appetizers
directions: Dry pickles with paper towel.
Spread cream cheese evenly over pickles.
Wrap slices of beef around pickles.
Slice into 1/4-inch coins.

title: stir-fried shrimp and rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 10-inch skillet; add shrimp and stir-fry over medium-high heat only until shrimp turn pink. Remove shrimp from pan and set aside.
Place onion and peppers in pan and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add chicken bouillon and stir 1 minute.
Stir in beaten eggs and stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat; season with soy sauce and peppers.
Place shrimp and rice on serving dish.
Top with green onions.
Serves 4.

title: orange slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for 2 to 3 minutes; let cool.
Blend with rest of ingredients and freeze.

title: orange-cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin slices.
Combine teriyaki baste and glaze, orange juice and wine; set aside.
Heat oil in hot wok or large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, green pepper and celery; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour in baste and glaze mixture; cook and stir until chicken and vegetables are coated with sauce. Remove from heat.
Stir in orange segments and cashews.
Serve immediately.

title: monte cristo sandwich
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
For each sandwich, cover slice of bread with cheese, ham and second slice of cheese.
Top with bread.
Dip sandwich in egg mixture.
Brown in skillet on both sides
in margarine.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Serve with jelly.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: tuna potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and cut up in cubes.
Add tuna, green beans and mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Spread half of the cabbage in a greased casserole.
Saute onion in a large frypan sprayed with butter flavored spray.
Add rice and brown.
Pour over cabbage.

title: molded cantaloupe cream
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in 3/4 cup orange juice and ginger; cool.
Chill until as thick as unbeaten egg white.

title: sweet easy pickles
directions: Let cucumbers set in salt water for 5 days.
Drain and wash. Add alum in water to cover pickles.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash.
Cover pickles with vinegar.
Let stand 24 hours. Drain.
Put pickles back in jug.
Pour sugar over pickles.
Leave in jug.
Does not have to be sealed.
May add pickling spice, if desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: vegetable chili
directions: In a 5-quart pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring often, until softened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add yellow squash, zucchini, red and green pepper, celery, mushrooms and carrots.
Cook, stirring often, until vegetables are crisp-tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, peas, wine, tomato paste, chili powder, cumin, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll each piece of biscuit in the sugar and cinnamon and place in angel food pan. Mix oleo and brown sugar very well and pour over the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and turn over.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Spread on cookie sheet (ungreased) and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook yams in skin until tender, then drain, peel and mash. Gradually add sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk while beating. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Mix together in a big bowl, except for almond bark. Melt almond bark over very low heat; stir often so it won't stick to pan and burn. When melted, pour over other ingredients and mix together. Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper. Makes a large amount. Can do ahead.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables and oil.
Boil vinegar and sugar to rolling boil 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats and set aside to cool.
Cream white sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, salt, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Add with oats mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all of the above and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, white and brown sugars, eggs and 1 stick melted margarine in casserole bowl.
Sprinkle cornflakes on mixture, then sprinkle pecans over cornflakes.
Pour 3/4 melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Flatten rolls.
Fill with mixture made from cream cheese, chicken, lemon pepper and mushrooms.
Brush with melted butter. Roll in crushed herb croutons and chopped pecans (optional).
Bake at 375° until brown, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Warm the mushroom soup; pour over baked rolls.

title: swiss eggs
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with cheese slices.
Break eggs over top of cheese slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour cream over eggs.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake until the eggs are desired doneness (soft or hard in the yolks).

title: nova's cheese balls
directions: Combine ingredients; save 1 cup pecans.
Form into 2 balls. Roll in remaining nuts to cover.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit duff
directions: Combine fruit choice, sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in medium bowl; mix well.
Pour into deep dish pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° until cream mixture is firm and fruit is soft, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add cream and flour.
Mix all together.
Roll dough mixture into strips or you may cut the dough into strips.
Bake the cheese straws at 400° until they are a delicate brown.

title: crab casserole
directions: Grease a 16-inch baking dish and put in 1/2 bread crumbs.
Mix crab meat, mayonnaise, onion, pepper, celery and pimento and place on bread cubes.
Put remaining bread cubes on crab mixture.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over casserole; let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, cover with undiluted soup and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Add cheese and paprika and bake 10 minutes.

title: black joke pie
directions: Melt chocolate bits and put in unbaked pie shell.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chocolate mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: low-cal quiche
directions: Beat together eggs and egg whites. Stir in remaining ingredients. Spray an 8-inch pie plate with nonstick spray and pour in mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, press out rolls, filling in any holes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese; layer with sliced sausage.
Pour egg and milk mixture and spices over top.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 18 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan except broccoli and rice and heat until melted.
Pour over broccoli and rice in baking dish and cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea and strain.
Add sugar and cool. Mix orange juice, lemon juice, pineapple juice and ginger ale. Add to tea.
Serve over ice.
You may garnish with sliced fruit and cherries, if you like.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: ruby's lemon pecan pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix with food in whisk.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: perfection pie crust
directions: Makes one double crust or two singles.
Preheat oven to 400°. Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut in shortening with a pastry cutter until mixture is in crumbs the size of peas.
Blend together egg, vinegar and water.
With a fork, lightly blend liquids into flour mixture to form a soft dough.
Fit into pans. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lollipops
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water until a little dropped in cold water becomes brittle.
Add coloring and flavoring and stir. Pour big drops of candy onto an oiled surface and insert sticks or use oiled metal candy molds and insert the sticks.

title: granny wicker's fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit and coat well with cake mix.
Add eggs, cinnamon and pie filling; mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil; mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: mandarin salad
directions: In small pan over medium heat, cook the almonds and sugar, stirring constantly, until almonds are coated with the melted sugar.
Cool.
Mix lettuce, celery and onions.
Just before serving, add almonds and oranges.
Toss with dressing.

title: tex-mex party soup
directions: Heat butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Saute carrots, celery and/or peppers until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add soup, milk, picante sauce and cumin.
Stir until smooth and hot.
Do not boil and stir frequently.
Reduce heat to warm.
Add cheeses and stir until melted.
Serves 4 to 6 (5 cups).

title: applesauce bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Soak bread crumbs in milk. Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Spoon the applesauce mixture into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean. Serve hot or cold.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Quickly brown pork chops and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with potatoes.
Mix soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are tender.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Marinate in oil for 1 to 2 hours, turning often.
Combine other ingredients in a large shallow dish. Roll chicken in mixture and place in greased, shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until crisp and tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into little balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Need a large bowl with a lid.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients (in order) in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients; pour over chicken. Bake, covered, until chicken is done, about 1 hour.

title: chickpea bread spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Slice the bread in half lengthwise. Brush the cut side with olive oil and bake 15 to 20 minutes until toasted. Combine in a blender jar or food processor the remaining ingredients; puree to a paste. Spread on the bread; garnish with the parsley and slice into serving size pieces. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken pie
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onion and celery until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, milk and Worcestershire until well-blended.
Add chicken, mixed vegetables and potato.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Spoon into 2-quart oval or 12 x 8-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: turkey-vegetable medley(low cholesterol - low-fat)
directions: In a large pan sprayed with Pam, cook the turkey until broken apart and browned.
Add all other ingredients, including some fluid from the canned vegetables to make a sauce.
Cover and simmer just 10 minutes.

title: smoked oyster roll
directions: Cream the cheese with mayonnaise and seasonings.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Chop oysters.
Place strip of Saran Wrap on cookie sheet.
Anchor with Scotch tape.
Spread cheese mixture into a rectangle, approximately 9 x 12-inch and less than 1/4-inch thick.
Spread chopped oysters over cheese.
Sprinkle walnuts over oysters.
Place cookie sheet in refrigerator about 15 minutes. Beginning at narrow end, roll cheese, jelly roll fashion.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: noodles and beef
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add other seasonings.
Drain fat from beef.
Cook noodles.
Add noodles to ground beef.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Combine all together and serve.

title: cajun crawfish cornbread
directions: You may substitute 1 pound ground chuck for the crawfish tails.

title: chocolate brittle
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Stir in cinnamon and 2 cups cereal; blend thoroughly.
Turn into large bowl; stir remaining cereal until completely coated.
Press into a waxed paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 to 2 hours until firm.
Cut with knife into pieces.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix in large punch bowl.
Let sherbet dissolve a little, not completely.
Serve immediately.

title: old fashioned butter cake
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla; add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition. Combine flour with baking soda and salt; add to batter alternately with buttermilk; beginning and ending with flour.
Butter and flour an 8-cup fluted mold.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until a tester inserted in center comes out clean. Allow cake to stand 5 minutes inverted; remove cake from pan and finish cooling on a cake rack.
Dust with powdered sugar before serving.

title: taco sauce
directions: Pick red and green peppers,
wash, cut off stems and dry good. Pour red or white
vinegar
(hot)
over peppers.
If you want hot pepper sauce, take 1
teaspoon
of
olive
oil and put over peppers before you seal bottle.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip and coconut and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Toast coconut and garnish top.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Cook 1 minute at a hard boil, then add 3 cups quick oats. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: amish raisin sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients until raisins are plump and sugar dissolved.
Thicken with cornstarch and water mixture.
Serve hot over ham.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and Bisquick until crumbly. Stir in milk until dough forms.
Beat 15 strokes.
Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on greased pan.
Make dent in cookies with spoon. Fill with jelly. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Glaze with confectioners sugar, water and vanilla, mixed together.

title: aunt thelma's hot dog sauce
directions: Cook onions until tender and mash.
Cook ground chuck just until gray.
Do Not Brown.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook until thick or can cook in larger cooker, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool and put into containers in freezer and use as needed. Can use 1/2 butter bowls.
This will make 3 to 4 hot dogs.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine in top of double boiler. When melted, pour over Rice Chex.
After all ingredients are mixed well, add powdered sugar and mix again. Pour onto large cookie sheet to cool.

title: potato and pea curry
directions: In small skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add potatoes and tomatoes and saute for 5 minutes.
Add peas, curry powder and salt, then stir in water.
Cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally, until potatoes and peas are tender, about 25 minutes (if necessary, add more water to prevent sticking). Makes 2 servings.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Mix applesauce, oil and sugar.
Sift in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add the egg and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with just enough milk to make a thick mixture.
Wet hands and roll mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Drop into real hot deep fat and remove when brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut up chicken in bite size pieces and place in a large casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex pan).
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed. Sprinkle over chicken.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: Grind enough onions to yield 1 1/2 gallons.
Add 1/4 cup of the salt and let stand 30 minutes.
Squeeze juice from onion-salt mixture and discard.

title: shirley's banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with mashed bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix cream-style corn, corn bread mix and sour cream well.
Add 2 eggs; again, mix well.
put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fry meat, onion and garlic in butter and season with salt and sweet basil.
Drain and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with zucchini slices and top each slice with some Velveeta cheese.
Add one more layer of zucchini.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Spread this over the top; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: limed cucumbers
directions: Whisk together lime rind and juice, oil, salt and pepper in bowl.
Add cucumber.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Heat margarine and oil in oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in a 400° oven until margarine melts.
Place chicken in dish, turning to coat with margarine mixture.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: jerome cookies
directions: Place a layer of whole graham crackers in an oblong dish.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in square baking pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nippy pork chop platter
directions: Spread pork chops with thin coating of mustard.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Shake bag to coat chops with flour.
Brown in melted fat in heavy skillet.
Place chops in baking dish.
Cover with soup.
Bake in oven (350°) for 40 minutes.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients into a bowl and let stand for 20 minutes.
Then add eggs, sugar, vanilla and mix.
Then add flour and pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Pour in 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Pour melted oleo on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: minute fudge
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan, place first five ingredients.
Mix over medium flame until Crisco melts.
Raise heat to high and bring to a fast rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Time 1 minute. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir or beat until thickened. Add chopped pecans and stir.
Pour quickly onto lightly buttered shallow dish.
When set completely, cut into squares and top with a pecan half.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine 1/4 cup flour and granulated sugar; mix with rhubarb.
Put into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine oats, 1 1/2 cups flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter. Crumble over top of rhubarb.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream.

title: bohemian stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken diane
directions: In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat half of the margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add chicken and cook, turning frequently, until lightly browned on all sides and, when pierced with a fork, juices run clear.
Remove chicken to a plate and keep warm.
In same skillet, heat remaining margarine until bubbly and hot; add onion and saute until translucent, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through.
Return chicken to skillet and turn to coat with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with hot rice and green salad.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prick pie shell and bake for 5 minutes at 400°; cool.
Mix cheese, bacon and onion and place in shell.
Mix rest of ingredients well and pour on top of cheese, bacon and onion.
Bake at 375° for 30
to 35 minutes or until center is firm.

title: fried chicken
directions: Beat the milk, salt and eggs together.
Pour over the chicken pieces.
Soak the chicken 3 to 4 hours.
Remove the pieces and shake the chicken in a bag containing the flour, pepper, soup stock powder and season salt.
Fry in 1/4-inch deep hot oil until crisp.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix oleo and crackers together.
Put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ritzy onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions.
Put into cold water and bring to a boil. Drain.
Add more water and salt; cook until transparent. Drain.
Place onions and butter in casserole and cool.
Add cheese and sprinkle crackers over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except half of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Melt butter; blend in onion and curry.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in broth and then milk.
Return to heat and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp.
Serve over rice.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in 1 3/4 cups water 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Moisten with remaining 1/4 cup cold water and add to raisins.
Stir until mixture boils.
Remove from fire and add butter and vinegar.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover top with pastry.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt together milk, butter and sugar.
Dissolve yeast (add to first mixture when cool).

title: savory onion chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter.
Coat with dry soup mix.
Arrange chicken skin side up with meaty pieces to the outside of the dish. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 18 to 22 minutes until meat is tender.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: overnight salad(serves 50)
directions: Prepare the day before needed for use.
Place in a refrigerator overnight.
Place milk in double boiler.
When warm, add eggs, mustard and salt.
Cook until thick.
Remove from stove and add lemon juice.

title: homestyle ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Adjust seasoning.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Makes
1 1/4 c. 30 calories per tablespoon.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add diced apples.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Add this to apple mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan and bake for 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.
Serve it hot, warm or cold.
Try it plain, frosted or with whipped cream.
Enjoy!

title: cracker jack
directions: Boil mixture until it turns a light brown in center.
(Be careful not to scorch).
Remove to back of stove and add the salt, vanilla and soda.
Also add butter.
Stir well and pour over popcorn that has been previously popped.
Stir corn until well coated and turn out to cool.

title: chile con queso
directions: Saute the onion in margarine.
Chop the tomatoes and chilies. Reserve the tomato juice from the canned tomatoes to thin if needed.
Simmer the onion, tomato and chilies for 15 minutes.
Add the cheese and cook until melted. Thin with tomato juice if needed.
Serve with nachos or Tostitos.
Can be frozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean.

title: "mom's" chocolate gravy
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Heat the milk to scalding; stir in flour mixture slowly.
Cook over low heat until thickens. Serve over hot biscuits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, real well and form into a ball. Roll in chipped pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Add 1/2 pint sour cream.
Pour over ingredients in casserole; top with rest of noodles.
Bake 1 hour or less at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit in colander.
Add sour cream and marshmallows. Toss (mix) around.
Add coconut, if desired.
Let stay overnight but not necessary.

title: no fat banana bread
directions: Mix together with spoon the sugar, bananas, applesauce and eggs.
Stir in flour, nuts, baking soda, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: red cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add red food coloring mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add by hand the vinegar and baking soda.
Line 2 round cake pans with wax paper (bottoms, grease well).
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: raggedy ann pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Mix until sugar dissolves. Place vegetables in pan and mix thoroughly.
Pour sugar mixture over vegetables and bring to a boil.
Stir and put in jars and seal at once.
Do not boil over 2 minutes for firmness.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour and onion.
Add egg and sugar.
Gradually stir in milk.
Drop from spoon into fat; fry until golden.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: (meatless) taco salad
directions: Mix beans, peppers, onions, tomatoes and cheese together. Just before serving, crunch Doritos and add to bean mixture.
Add dressing; stir and eat.

title: chicken with duck sauce
directions: Put chicken in open roaster.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread over chicken.
Bake 2 hours, uncovered, at 300°.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk over medium heat; stir constantly until smooth. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust.

title: baked curried cauliflower
directions: Heat 1 inch water to boil in covered saucepan.
Add cauliflower and salt; cook 10 minutes, no longer.
Drain well. Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder in 2-quart casserole.
Add cauliflower; mix well.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle over dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no guilt potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and cool.
Drain potatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix.
Coat vegetables with the dressing. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Place first six ingredients into a Dutch oven and heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to crock-pot and add canned vegetables.
Heat on high for 1 hour, then reduce heat to low and cook at least 2 to 3 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: party punch
directions: Mix frozen grape juice, frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade, water and ice cubes together.
Just before you are ready to serve the punch, slowly pour in the ginger ale.
Pour punch into a big punch bowl and serve.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting the salt; drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli in 10x6x1 1/2 inch baking dish.
Combine soup and cheese, add milk, mayonnaise and egg gradually, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli, combine margarine and bread crumbs; sprinkle evenly over soup mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are lightly browned.
Garnish with parsley.

title: green mango chutney
directions: Sprinkle 2 teaspoons salt over diced mangos and let sit.
Add raisins to 1 cup dark rum and soak until rum absorbed.
Combine vinegar and sugar and bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Add mangos and cook over low heat until tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer on high for 1/2 hour.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 1 hour.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: lemonade soy chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in shallow baking dish; pour lemonade/soy mixture over chicken.
Heat oven to 400°; place dish on top rack.
After 10 minutes, baste with the apricot juice. After 10 more minutes, turn over chicken.
Baste after 10 more minutes; cook another 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O, oil, water, eggs and 2/3 cup strawberries.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 2 cake pans; cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool 10 to 15 minutes before icing.
Refrigerate.
Can use already prepared icing; can decorate with fresh strawberries.

title: sausage rings
directions: Spread sausage over both pie crusts.
Roll up and spread roll to the size of a nickle.
Place in freezer and freeze until hardened enough to slice.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom of 10-inch tube or fluted tube pan that has been greased and floured or sprayed with Pam. Combine remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Prepare Glaze. Invert cake onto serving plate.
Prick with cake tester or wooden pick and carefully spoon warm glaze over warm cake.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy glazed nuts
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg white lightly and stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in water. Blend well.
Add nuts about 1/2 cup at a time.
Using a fork, stir to coat nuts well.
Lift out; drain, then place on greased baking sheet, separating each nut meat.
Bake at 275° until golden crusty, about 45 minutes.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: banana bread
directions: Bring butter and eggs to room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar until very creamy.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add buttermilk to mashed bananas.
Pour mixture into batter quickly.
Stir well.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Lay chicken in sheet cake pan.
Pour uncooked rice over all the chicken.
Spoon the soups over the chicken and rice, then pour a can of milk over all.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, or until chicken is done.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
In a bowl, mash bananas and thawed strawberries, crushed pineapple and Jell-O mixture.
Pour half of this mixture into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Refrigerate until mixture has set.
Take out of refrigerator, spread sour cream and add remaining mixture over this and refrigerate again.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish layer slices of corned beef, scrunch them up not a slab.
Drain sauerkraut of 1/2 its juice, lay onto corned beef.
Top with swiss cheese and bake at 350° for 10 minutes until cheese in melted but not liquidy.
While baking mix Thousand Island dressing, mayonnaise, and relish.
Remove casserole, cut into 4 servings, top with dressing.
From low carb luxury.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut in quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water.
Shake, a few at a time, in bag, coating with cheese mix.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in a large salad bowl in order appearing above.
Spread Miracle Whip over the top of ingredients covering well and sealing everything in.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top of Miracle Whip. Sprinkle top with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight 24 hours.
Toss together just before serving.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together warm milk, flour, yeast and sugar to make a sponge. Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1/2 hour. Add the eggs, oil and salt to sponge and mix well. Then add flour, 2 cups at a time until you have a nice, soft dough. Cover and let rise again until double in bulk. Dump out on floured board. Knead a few minutes. Then roll out in oblong shape. Spread melted butter over dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Cover with raisins and nuts, if desired. Roll up into long roll. Slice or cut with a string. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until browned. (Frost, if desired.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Save broth to boil spaghetti in.
Debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Drain spaghetti.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Add soups, cheese and Ro-Tel diced tomatoes.
Mix well.
Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons juice.
Rub chicken with garlic; sprinkle with salt.
Broil or grill chicken until cooked through.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, honey, lime juice, soy sauce and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add pineapple to sauce.
Cook until heated through.
Spoon sauce and pineapple over chicken.
Sprinkle with lime peel.
Serves 4.

title: cool whip cake
directions: For crust, mix flour, butter and pecans; pat mixture in pan with dampened fingers.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
First layer mix cool whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese; beat until fluffy. Spread over crust by spoonfuls.
Then add pudding mixture over first layer; then top with cool whip.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.
Pudding mix can be any flavor you desire.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package as 2 layers.
In a punch bowl or large bowl, slice cake into 4 layers or use short cake. Begin layers with cake. Add a layer of each in this order:
pineapple, strawberries, bananas, pudding and Cool Whip. Repeat for 4 layers. Chill at least 4 hours; overnight is best!

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine seasonings
with peppers and onions and boil 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: green salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: refrigerated dessert
directions: Cut butter and flour until crumbly.
Add 3/4 cup peanuts. Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
In small bowl, blend softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and half of frozen topping.
Spread over crust and chill. Mix chocolate and coffee flavored pudding mixes with milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill or freeze until firm.
Top with additional whipped topping, sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup chopped peanuts and add shaved chocolate over top.
Serves 16.

title: sweet and sour scallops
directions: Slice green pepper into strips.
Place scallops and vegetables in a pan with the bottle of sauce.
Place in 400° oven, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until scallops are tender.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into pan.
Mix remaining 5 ingredients together and spread this topping on batter in pan.
Bake in a greased 9 x 15-inch cake pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep covered in refrigerator. Let set at least 24 hours before baking. Do not stir.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 to 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: Melt margarine; add flour, heat and stir until light-colored and bubbly.
Do not brown.
Add milk, stir until it thickens.
Add more or less milk to make it the thickness you like.
Cut beef into 1/2-inch squares, or tear it into small pieces.
Add to sauce. Make toast.
Spoon sauce on toast.
Serves 6 or will serve 1 person 6 times for breakfast by reheating in microwave.

title: red neck caviar
directions: Prepare ingredients as listed and mix together. Refrigerate several hours or overnight for flavors to blend. Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp dejonge
directions: Peel and saute shrimp quickly with the butter in a hot pan. Add flour, shallots, sherry and cream.
Allow to cook gently about 5 minutes.
Pour into au gratin dish; cover with the Dejonge Butter.
Place under the broiler until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: candy-coated carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in a small amount of water until crisp-tender.
Drain and keep warm.
In the same saucepan, cook butter and brown sugar until bubbly.
Stir in lemon juice and salt.
Return carrots and heat through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cajun seafood jambalaya
directions: In a Dutch oven, saut sausage and ham until it begins to brown. Add butter, chopped vegetables and garlic; saut until soft, stirring often. Stir in seasoning, stock and tomatoes and bring to a boil. Add rice, stirring well. Add seafood; stir and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is done, about 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: christmas soup
directions: Bring to a boil and serve.

title: cinnamon orange chicken
directions: Coat chicken in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and cinnamon. Heat margarine in large frying pan.
Add chicken and saute for 20 minutes or until tender and golden all over.
Remove chicken and drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.
Pour off fat from pan.
Add chicken broth and finely grated rind and juice of 1 orange.
Bring to a boil, whisking constantly.
Arrange chicken on serving platter.
Pour sauce on top.
Peel remaining orange removing skin and pith; slice thinly.
Arrange orange slices on chicken and serve with rice.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat the oil, sugar, milk, vanilla extract, almond extract, butter extract and eggs well.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, salt and poppy seed and add to first mixture.
Mix all together and pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Glaze while warm.

title: fruit punch
directions: Heat water and sugar.
Mix lemons, pineapple juice, orange juice and bananas.
Add ginger ale right before serving.
Serves a crowd.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On top of stove, melt margarine.
Saute onions in melted margarine.
Add mushrooms undrained.
Add rice and stir until warm, then add consomme stirring until warm.
Put in large baking dish and cover.
Bake for 1 hour.
After baking for about 30 minutes, stir well and return to oven to continue cooking.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash lettuce and chop.
Put in a good size bowl.
Sprinkle the green onions on top.
Mix together vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Have the bacon and drippings hot.
Pour vinegar and sugar mixture over the lettuce and mix to coat.
Take the hot bacon and drippings and pour over the lettuce right before serving.

title: pancake mix
directions: Sift this together and store in a dry place.

title: quicky carbonara
directions: Brown bacon.
Remove and cool.
In same pan, brown ham strips in bacon grease, olive oil and butter, adding crushed garlic clove.
Add spaghetti, crumbled bacon, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Pour eggs over and quickly toss to coat spaghetti.
Turn off heat.
Ad olives, if desired and mix in. Serve immediately.

title: strawberry fudge balls
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add melted chocolate beating until smooth.
Stir in wafer crumbs and preserves.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll the balls in almond or powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: calico corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour hot into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps; process 15 minutes in boiling water bath. Yields 6 half pints.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: Next day heat and add 1 cup of sugar.
Heat 3 mornings adding 1 cup of sugar each time.
Can on the 3rd morning.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and heavy cream in a heavy 6-quart saucepan.
Cook over low flame, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Raise flame to medium heat and continue cooking, stirring frequently, until small amounts form a 238° soft ball in cold water.
Remove from flame.
Beat immediately.
Beat until candy begins to harden.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and cherries and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add applesauce, raisins and nutmeats.
Sift flour, soda and spices together and add to mixture gradually;
beat after each addition.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil until all liquid is gone, stirring as it boils.
Spread peanuts on shallow pan and cook in oven at 250° for 10 minutes.
Stir and cook another 10 minutes. Cool and enjoy.

title: old southern cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg.
Alternately add flour, salt and raisin mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in loaf pan in moderate oven at 350°
until done.

title: soft sugar cookies and icing
directions: Sift the dry ingredients.
Add shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Roll out on floured surface.
Don't roll too thin.
Bake in 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Stir in milk and water; mix well. Stir in remaining flour (batter will be soft). Do not knead. Spray 3 (13 ounce) coffee cans or 8 1/2 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans with nonstick spray. Sprinkle with corn meal. Spoon batter in pans; sprinkle corn meal on top. Cover; let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from cans to cool on wire rack. Yield: 3 loaves.

title: by cracky bars
directions: Sift the Flour, Salt and Baking Soda.
Blend Spry and Sugar and cream well.
Add Eggs; beat well.
Combine Milk and Vanilla; add with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Place more than 1/3 of batter in a second bowl and add melted Chocolate and Nuts.
Spread in pan.
Arrange Graham Crackers over batter.
Add Bits to remaining batter.
Drop by spoonfuls over crackers and spread. Bake at 375 for 20 - 25 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together, in 3-quart glass baking dish, all of the ingredients, except the bacon.
Place the bacon across the top.

title: potato souffle
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes and mix all together.
Put in buttered casserole.
Bake covered 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover.
Bake until brown, about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally as souffle bakes and allow to cool a bit before serving.

title: pork chops-white wine-orange juice
directions: Rub chops with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour.
Brown in fat at 350° edges first, then sides. Add wine, up to about the middle of the chops and cook at 275° for about an hour.
Add a chunk of frozen orange juice to each chop and cook one half hour more.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bonbon cups
directions: Melt 4 squares of the chocolate in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, milk and corn syrup.
Stir in fruits and extract.
Spoon into 3 dozen paper bonbon cups; chill.
Melt remaining 4 squares chocolate with butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Cool slightly.
Spoon onto fruit filling in cups, mounding the chocolate.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: united states senate restaurant bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
In a large pot, put beans, 4 quarts water and ham hock.
Boil slowly for approximately 3 hours. Braise chopped onion in a little butter. When onion is light brown, add to bean soup.
Season with salt and pepper; serve. Serves 8.

title: dirt cake dessert
directions: You will need one 8-inch flowerpot with plastic flowers or tall bowl or maybe a sand bucket and shovel.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter. Beat in milk.
Gradually fold in whipped cream.
Fill pie shell. Sprinkle with chocolate shavings or chopped peanuts if desired. Can be served either frozen or chilled.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of a double boiler.
Stir in milk; cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks. Gradually stir in hot mixture.
Return to double boiler.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: griffin's favorite cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in a pan on stove. Bring to a boil (stirring often) for 1 minute. Add other ingredients one at a time, stirring well. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper. Cool. Makes a yummy batch of cookies!!

title: salisbury steak with onion gravy
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup soup in a bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 6 oval patties.
Brown in skillet and drain.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet. Saute onion and celery.
Add frozen broccoli, turning until thawed.
Add rice, milk, soup, Cheez Whiz and almonds.
Mix well. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes and ham in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over potatoes and ham.
Top with crushed chips or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: You will need 4 pint jars.

title: holiday bavarian dip
directions: Cut the braunschweiger into small pieces.
Add the sour cream and the onion soup mix to the braunschweiger in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth and well blended.

title: peach, orange and ginger fizz(makes four 10 ounce servings)
directions: Thaw the peaches according to package directions.
Puree in a food processor or blender.
Divide the peach puree evenly among four tall glasses.
Add 1/2 cup of orange juice to each glass and ice cubes, if desired.
Top off with a slow stream of ginger ale. Stir gently to mix.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; let stand in cold water overnight.
Pack into hot sterilized jars.
To each quart, add 1/8 teaspoon alum.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Mix cornmeal, flour and baking powder well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk until all is well blended. Pour into a well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done in the middle.
This is moist and tasty and better than most cornmeal breads.

title: fasta pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente, drain and cool.
In large bowl, combine ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: light and fluffy pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly with a fork and let sit for 5 to 7 minutes. Fry pancakes with a small amount of oil, just as you would with regular pancakes.

title: live-longer casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
In a medium bowl mix together spinach, tomatoes, zucchini and salt (optional); add to onion-mushroom mixture. Simmer 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti 15 minutes in boiling water, drain and add to vegetable mixture.
Spray 9 x 13-inch casserole with cooking spray; pour vegetable mixture into casserole.
Mix cheeses together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat; stir frequently.
Add food coloring. Don't overcook.
Remove from pan and onto wax paper when it starts to harden.
Knead in a little flour when cooled.
Store in an airtight container.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut salt pork into 1/2 cubes.
Cook in large kettle until crispy.
Remove bits and reserve.
To hot pork fat, add onions. Cook until tender, stirring often.
Top with potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour on boiling water.
Top with fish cut into medium pieces.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and evaporated milk.
Sprinkle with parsley. Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook lean, raw beef in 2-inches of water with soup mix for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often. Add the broth, vegetables, carrots, tomato, potatoes and salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Bring to boil in 16-quart pot.
Fill 1/2 full of water.
Add salt and pepper, Old Bay seasoning and onions to taste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add cut up sausage; cook 45 minutes on medium heat. Bring to boil again.
Add corn and potatoes when almost tender. Add peeled shrimp.

title: rhonda's fabulous cookies
directions: *For chocolate chip cookies, use a white cake mix and milk chocolate chips.
For orange cookies, use orange cake mix.
For lemon cookies, use lemon cake mix.
For chocolate cookies, use chocolate cake mix.
For strawberry cookies, use strawberry cake mix.

title: pineapple jello
directions: Drain juice from pineapple to make the 2 cups of water to put in jello.
Let jello set, then mix pineapple and cream cheese. Fold into jello, then let finish setting.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Add cream of tartar, then flour.
Dough will be stiff.
Make in 4 to six rolls in waxed paper.
Refrigerate overnight; slice in 3/8-inch slices. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes; do not overbake.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Make into small balls.
Pour tomato sauce over top of meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy!

title: stefanie's bran muffins
directions: Dissolve the baking soda in 1 cup boiling water; set aside to cool.
Cream butter and sugar together, then add eggs.
Stir in by hand the remaining ingredients.
Finally, stir in the soda water. Bake in muffin pans at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out very thin and cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 400° for about 9 minutes.
Run spatula under cookies immediately after removing pan to prevent sticking.
These are inexpensive and the children love them.

title: braided chicken roll
directions: On cookie sheet unroll dough and place all four rectangles of dough down center of cookie sheet.	Press seams together making about a 9 inch piece of dough.
Combine all other ingredients and place on center of dough.
Cut sides of dough in halves, then quarters, then thirds, criss cross over top of filling.
Pinch together at ends and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onions in a large skillet.
Pour off the fat that accumulates.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well, and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Spoon onto buns.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Grind all ingredients.
Put in large pan.
As you put salt in, keep tasting the mixture.
When you can taste the salt, stir up good, then put in container and freeze.

title: swedish nut cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: crunchies
directions: Microwave brown sugar, butter and corn syrup until boiling. Add vanilla and baking soda; stir. Put cereal and nuts on pan and drizzle syrup mixture over. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Cool on paper towels, breaking the pieces apart.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Butter large casserole. Put potatoes in bottom and pour mixture on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except for the nuts) in a bowl and let chill for 30 minutes. Form into 2 balls and roll in the chopped nuts. Cover with plastic wrap and store in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Take 3/4 of mixture and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: shrimp-oyster gumbo
directions: Cook onion and red pepper in butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add flour and brown lightly.
Add water, tomatoes and gumbo file. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add okra, shrimp and oysters. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Mix
soup,
sour
cream, poppy seed, salt and pepper. Pour
over
chicken
in casserole dish. Crush crackers and mix with
melted
butter.
Place
on top of chicken mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oil cake . . . dark and moist!
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients at once with electric mixer (do not add eggs until last!).
Bake in large 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
If using a metal pan, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If using a glass pan, bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Also makes 30 cupcakes.
Dust with powdered sugar just before serving or top with Cool Whip topping or a frosting of your choice.

title: healthful date bread
directions: In
a
medium
mixing
bowl, combine dates and raisins. Pour boiling water mixture and set aside to cool slightly.
In large mixing
bowl,
stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir egg whites and vanilla into cooled date mixture.
Add date mixture and almonds to flour mixture; stir until well blended.
Mixture will be thick.
Evenly spread the batter into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake in
350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted
into
the center
comes
out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove
from pan;
cool
thoroughly on a wire rack. Wrap
and
store
overnight before serving.
Makes 1 loaf, 18 servings.
Contains no added sugar, fat or cholesterol!

title: bacon cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Set aside. Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring until soda dissolves.
Add buttermilk mixture, bacon and cheese to flour mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream butter and flour; add rest of ingredients.
Form into balls; place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press balls out with a wet fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Mix remaining ingredients with browned meat.
Spread mixture on a half hamburger bun.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a saucepan, blend butter and flour; gradually add milk and seasonings.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Place asparagus and stock in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Cover with cream sauce. Sprinkle with pimento and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Bake.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions in plate.
Combine remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted
in center comes out clean.
Cool five minutes.

title: italian salad
directions: Cut salami halves into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Pour dressing over combined salami, vegetables and tomatoes.
Toss lightly.
Cover marinade in refrigerator several hours.
Add cheese and toss lightly just before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart in ungreased sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: banana split
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas crosswise; layer over crumbs.
Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch slices and place over bananas.
Sprinkle ice cream with walnuts; freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add powdered sugar and milk.
Cook (bring to a boil); take from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool chocolate mixture; pour over ice cream.
Freeze until firm.

title: chicken francese
directions: Pound chicken 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Dredge eggs in flour mixed with salt and pepper, then dip in beaten eggs.
Heat oil and butter in skillet.
Cook each piece of chicken until golden on each side.

title: green chile dip
directions: Mix all together; marinate for at least an hour.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In medium size bowl, mix all the ingredients together well. Put in refrigerator for 1 or 2 hours.
Remove from refrigerator, form into croquettes and pan fry in butter on high until browned on both sides.
Then, lower heat and let simmer until croquettes are done.
(While simmering, you may want to add a little water to pan in order to keep croquettes moist.)

title: irish cream
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into jar with lid.
Keep refrigerated.
Stir once a day for 1 week.

title: lori's gourmet carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, measure flour.
Make a large hole in the center of the flour and add all ingredients at once and hand mix until thoroughly blended.
Grease and flour 1 large Bundt cake pan (or angel food cake pan or 2 large loaf pans).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
When cool, ice with a mixture of:

title: scalloped potatoes for 2
directions: Add Schnapps to first 2 ingredients.
Use the same flavor of jello as Schnapps (strawberry, peaches, etc.).

title: easy punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Add to this the large can of pineapple juice.
Pour over ice cubes which have been frozen with a red or green cherry inside.
Makes one gallon.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together. Store in airtight container. Use 1/2 cup mix to each cup hot water. Makes 44 cups.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Break cauliflower in flowerets; cook in small amount of water until tender.
Put 1/2 of cauliflower in baking dish.
Slice 2 boiled eggs and part of cheeses.
Repeat with rest of ingredients. Cover with white sauce and then bread crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Wash and dry romaine lettuce.
Pour dressing mix over lettuce and top with Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Leave green peppers whole and boil for 10 minutes.
Brown your hamburger and onions.
Boil your rice; drain your hamburger and onions.
Mix in with your cooked rice after drained.
Mix the tomato sauce in with the rice.
Use a large deep dish pan.
Put about half inch of water in the pan.
Put all the stuff in peppers; then set the pepper in pan.
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, chilies, sour cream, 2/3 of cheese and chicken together.
Roll in tortillas and put into pan.
Pour leftover mixture on top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(Leftover chicken, cut into squares, may be substituted for canned chicken.)

title: "creamy potato soup"
directions: Dice the potatoes and boil.
Meanwhile, put oil in bottom of Dutch oven and saute the diced celery and chopped onion just enough to soften.
Do not saute to a brown color.
Drain most of the water from potatoes and pour a small amount along with potatoes in the Dutch oven with the onion and celery.
Mash some of the potatoes into small bits.
Add milk, butter, salt, pepper and ham chunks.
Cover and simmer on low for 20 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally to keep from scorching on the bottom.

title: heavenly rice (2)
directions: Heat pineapple and juice in saucepan over medium heat.
Add jello and salt; stir until jello is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are partially melted.
Chill in freezer until mixture gets syrupy, stirring occasionally.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Whip chilled milk until thick, then add sugar.
Beat for 1 minute more.
Add Kool-Aid and beat for another minute.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and egg.
