Beat 5 minutes at medium speed on an electric mixer or until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour filling into crust. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Sprinkle this mixture over top of pie.
Bake 10 additional minutes.
Let cool on rack 5 minutes.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes one 9-inch pie or 6 servings.

title: peppermint chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave at 1/2 power for 1 minute.
Stir thoroughly.
Microwave and stir at 30 second intervals until smooth and completely melted. Stir in peppermint chips and pour out thin on wax paper on countertop.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Stir together egg whites, corn syrup, water and vanilla.
Stir in Baking Mix; blend well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Spread sugar on small flat plate.
Roll balls in sugar to coat.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet coated with nonstick spray.
Press balls flat with bottom of cup.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven but allow cookies to stay on pan for about 5 minutes.

title: sheath cake
directions: Add soda to 1/2 cup buttermilk and reserve.
Sift together flour and sugar.
Bring Crisco, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour the hot mixture over the dry ingredients and mix in the buttermilk mixture, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased, floured 11 x 16-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: avocado dip
directions: In blender, blend avocado, sour cream, green onions and lemon juice until smooth. Chill until time to serve.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 cups dip.

title: veal piccante
directions: Place 1/2 stick margarine in pan and heat and dip veal in flour lightly and season.
Brown on both sides, about 10 minutes in all, until veal whitens.
Place in hot dish.
Add remaining 1/2 stick of margarine, parsley and juice of one lemon to hot skillet and mix well to heat.
Add a little water if you wish more sauce. Pour over veal and serve.

title: "fake" lasagna
directions: Saute the meat, onions, peppers, tomato sauce and basil until meat is cooked and onions and peppers are soft.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream in a separate bowl. Cook and drain noodles.
Place alternate layers of noodles and cheese mixture in a casserole.
Put meat sauce on top and bake in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop vegetables any way you wish and add salt.
Let stand for 1 hour, then pour and squeeze off all liquids.
Add first mixture. Mix together well and put in cartons.
Freeze.
When you thaw, drain off liquid and add mayonnaise or dressing if you wish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with wire whisk.
Add salt, butter, syrup, sugar and vanilla mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown. Stir in the next 8 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add Italian meatballs.
Cover loosely; cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Pass Parmesan cheese. Serves 8.

title: nachos el grego
directions: Shred chicken very finely; add all seasonings.
Marinate 1 hour.
Heat oven to 450°.
Line glass pie pan with nacho chips. Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese (shredded), then add chicken; top with rest of cheese and add onions.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a heavy pan.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture forms a ball.
Knead ball of dough on counter for 1 minute.
Divide and knead in food coloring for colors of play dough you want to make.
Soak pan immediately in cold water.
Play dough will keep for several weeks in refrigerator in airtight containers.

title: apple-cheese bake
directions: Place apples in casserole dish.
Grate cheese over top. (Cheese grates better if frozen first.)
Cut the sugar, butter and flour with a pastry blender until like coarse meal.
Sprinkle over top of apples and cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: Combine 2 packages of beef, onion, cream cheese, Accent and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl.
Mix well and form into a ball. Roll ball in the remaining package of beef that has been chopped. Serve at room temperature.
Makes 1 very large cheese ball or 2 small cheese balls.
Two-thirds of this recipe makes a good size ball for a tray of crackers.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls on cookie sheet, spread out.
Let cool. Spread cream cheese on rolls.
Pat on veggies, cut into squares and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add crumbs.
In 2-quart casserole dish, layer thinly sliced squash, cheese and crumb mixture, ending with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put first four ingredients in a nonstick pan.
Cook all the ingredients until they come to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Turn off the heat.

title: golden glow jello salad
directions: Mix jello, waters and juice and let partially set.
Add pineapple and oranges.
When set, top with Cool Whip.
Dot with pecans.

title: grandkids' favorite french toast
directions: Spread six slices bread with peanut butter and six slices with jam.
Put slices together to form peanut butter and jam sandwiches; set aside.

title: arnaud's sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp.
Pour over shrimp; marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve ice cold shrimp over a bed of shredded lettuce on individual salad plates.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on pan.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine; spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: citrus punch(feeds a crowd)
directions: Combine lemonade mix, sugar and warm water.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Add ReaLemon juice, pineapple juice and water.
Pour into plastic containers and freeze.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix well for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Test after toothpick.

title: pork burritos(low-fat recipe)
directions: Slice pork loin into strips and stir-fry with onion in vegetable oil.
Stir in corn and toss with 2 teaspoons of taco seasoning.
Roll up portions in four warm tortillas.
Serve with salsa, rice and red beans.
Serves 4. Preparation and cooking time about 15 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Beat egg with fork in a cup.
Add vinegar and water and mix.
Pour over flour mixture and work together with hands.
Ready to roll out for pie.
Any trimmings can be rerolled.

title: fried squash blossoms
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, garlic and cumin.
In another bowl beat egg, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
In skillet, heat 2 inches of oil to 375°.
Dip blossoms into batter and fry in oil a few at a time until crispy.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: great roast beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over roast.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half into a 9x13 pan.
Drizzle melted butter over cookies and pat into pan.
Slice ice cream in 1/2 in. slices and lay on cookie crust.
Drizzle chocolate over ice cream. Spread cool whip over chocolate.
Sprinkle cookies on top. Freeze.

title: creamed ham and asparagus
directions: In saucepan cook asparagus in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating until mixture stands in peaks.
Add salt, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto glazed paper.
Bake 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool slightly before removing from paper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender; drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Mash. Combine reserved liquid and remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup stuffing mix.
Stir in squash.
Pour mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with reserved stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields about 16 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and salad oil, then add the pumpkin and eggs.
Sift together all dry ingredients, then add alternately with 2/3 cup water, 2/3 cups raisins (you can use cut up dates). This makes 2 loaves.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: great chow chow
directions: Add salt to tomatoes and let set 2 to 3 hours.
Drain off excess water.
Add chopped cabbage, onions, hot peppers (chopped) and 8 to 10 large sweet peppers (chopped).
Mix vinegar, sugar and pickling spice.
Add to vegetables and boil 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: souffled broccoli
directions: Trim and separate broccoli.
Cook in small amount of boiling, salted water for 10 minutes.
Melt butter and cook onions until soft.
Cut broccoli into chunks and puree with onions.
Put in bowl and blend in lemon juice, salt and 3/4 of cheese.
Fold in egg.
Spoon into buttered dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Melt butter.
Add spices.
Pour over sugar and mix.
When cool, add eggs.
Beat one hour.
Put one heaping teaspoon of mixture in cup.
Add a jigger of rum and fill cup with boiling water.
Freezes well.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until tender; let cool.
Remove from bones and cube.
Mix in bowl with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, olives, onions and 1 cup enchilada sauce.
Heat tortillas in about 1/2 inch of hot oil in a large skillet.
Remove tortillas from oil and dip in sauce.
Roll about 3 tablespoons of mixture into each tortilla and place in 1-inch deep ungreased baking pan. Spread remaining sauce on top of enchiladas.
Spread the remaining Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese on top.
May be topped with extra olives.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes; until all cheese is melted.
Makes approximately 36 enchiladas.

title: roast beef and cheddar pockets
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Remove as much gravy as possible from the roast beef and cut beef into fine shreds. Unroll crescent dough onto a baking sheet. Separate into 4 rectangles. Press diagonal seems to seal. Put beef, 2/3 c. cheese and onion in a large bowl and mix well. Divide mixture into quarters. Fix each quarter into a 1 inch log. Place meat into center of each rectangle. Fold long sides over log pressing each seam to seal. Sprinkle each pocket with remaining cheese. Bake for 13 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3 or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together in a frypan.
Simmer on low for about 5 minutes.
You can either refrigerate until needed or roll in shells and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (covered) about 20 minutes at 350°.
Use extra mixture over top of shells.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Put in 3 (9-inch) pans and bake until done. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: 1930's tomato cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in the 1/2 cup water.
Beat like any other cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creole chicken
directions: In a large 3-quart pot, melt butter and saute vegetables.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and seasonings.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Then add chicken and let simmer another 10 minutes. Serve over a bed of rice.

title: squash souffle
directions: Mix well.
Put in pan and bake in hot oven about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix milk, butter and eggs.
Pour the mixture in bottom of pan. Add macaroni to that, then spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with:

title: flaky never fail biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Cut in Crisco well.
Add milk and stir quickly with fork only until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn on lightly floured surface and knead gently with heel of hand.
Pat dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; chill.
Then peel and grate in large bowl.
In saucepan over low heat (or in microwave), put butter and cheese; stir until melted.
Remove from heat, blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over potatoes; mix well. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Add all ingredients together; stir to mix.
Simmer on medium-high for about 15 minutes or just long enough to heat okra through.
Do not boil.
Serve.

title: marge's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add remaining ingredients, including juices.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate to congeal.

title: whipped cream fruit dressing
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add remaining ingredients except cream. Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
When cold, fold in whipped cream.
Makes 2 cups.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put in a medium casserole dish.
Combine the melted margarine and crackers. Put the cracker/margarine mixture on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: harold's toast
directions: Cut bread slices in half and place on cookie sheet.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with garlic salt and celery salt. Toast at 350° for 20 minutes or until crisp and lightly browned. Can be made months ahead and stored in Tupperware.
Good to serve with hot cheese dip.

title: chocolate amaretto pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar in Amaretto.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell and freeze until firm.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: I think this makes the best grilled turkey sandwich in the world with some Swiss cheese.
I always make it for the holidays.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Pour flour, cornmeal, sugar and salt all in a bowl.
Mix well. Boil water.
Mix with hands or spoon; add hot water slowly so you can roll up as a ball and mash down.
Fry until good and brown in hot oil.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl combine mayo and sour cream, mixing until smooth.
Add spinach and veggie soup mix, blending thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.
Cover.
Cut off top of the bread.
Chop into pieces.
Pour mixture into bread and serve.

title: play dough
directions: Mix water, salt, flour and alum.
Add food coloring and oil.

title: pink cloud
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan. Heat to boiling. Remove from heat. Add gelatin and mix well.
Cool to room temperature, then stir in cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, vanilla, bananas and milk.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Do not stir any of the ingredients in the first step.
Sift cocoa and sugar in bowl.
Add milk and lay butter on top; do not stir.
Cook on High for 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion and clams in butter (15 minutes).
Mix soups, half and half and 1/2 of juice from clams (discard rest of juice). Cook on low in crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Soak cabbage in cold water 30 minutes.
Drain.
Mix 1 1/2 c. corn flakes together with melted butter.
Put in baking dish. Cover with drained cabbage.
Heat together mayonnaise, milk and celery soup.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with cheese and remaining corn flakes.

title: beef vegetable casserole
directions: Place ground beef in bottom of buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with dry onion mix and soup; add layers of other ingredients in order.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Drain pineapple and add juice to gelatin. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white. Stir in pineapple, coconut and pecans. Pour into lightly greased mold or individual molds. Chill until firm.

title: zucchini-rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
In a large skillet, heat butter and oil. Add onion and stir until tender. Add garlic and zucchini; stir 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and stir 1 minute longer. Stir in half and half, rice, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.

Pour into dish and sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake, uncovered, 20 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 10 to 20 minutes. The cooled, baked casserole can be tightly covered and refrigerated overnight or frozen.
Just thaw and bring to room temperature before reheating, covered, in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Add 6 cups water and 1 tablespoon soda.
Boil for 20 minutes; drain.
Rinse with boiling water.
Mix beans, catsup, molasses and sugar.
Fry sausages until lightly browned; cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix with
other ingredients.
Add boiling water.
Bake for 3 hours at 325°.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add coconut, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes until slightly browned.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crackers and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well peanut butter, sugar, egg and flour.
Use enough flour to powder hands and roll dough into small balls as big as silver dollar.
Press (lightly down) on the ball with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: holiday divinity
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Cover with a tight lid and bring to a boil.
Remove lid; place thermometer in pan and cook at 250° without stirring.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Break egg whites until soft peaks form. Add gelatin and beat into egg whites.
Pour hot syrup slowly over flavored beaten egg whites, beating constantly on high speed of electric mixer until soft peaks form and hold.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 70 candies.

title: hershey fudge
directions: Combine cocoa with sugar and salt. Add milk; bring to boil, stirring frequently. Cook to 232° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat. Drop in butter. Cool to lukewarm (110°). Add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens. Pour into buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: fluffy lemon pudding frosting
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add lemon Jell-O, instant pudding and pie filling and powdered sugar.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip, thawed.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil hen or fryer, cool and debone (keep stock).
In skillet saute onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Do not drain tomatoes, mushrooms or pimentos; use their juices.
Stir all together and add spaghetti and chicken. Stir in cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not drain spaghetti - this will be the liquid you need.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat oil. Saut onion, green pepper, mushrooms, garlic, basil, thyme, paprika, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Blend in tomatoes, broth, tomato sauce and bay leaves. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes. Add cut up Italian sausage. Simmer another 10 minutes. Add fish, frozen mussels and okra. Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes. Stir in shrimp; cook for an additional 3 minutes. Remove bay leaves.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Do not use the recipe on the box of cake mix.
The only ingredient from the box recipe you use is the amount of water. Substitute the listed ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet.
Add water, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Stir in pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 11 x 9-inch dish or pan in preheated oven.
In separate bowl, mix milk, sugar and flour.
Place fruit in pan over margarine.
Pour lemon juice over fruit.
Pour flour batter over fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in a 1-quart casserole or two-cup glass measure.
Stir in water.
Cook in microwave oven on full power for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time. Blend in butter.
Cook on full power for 30 seconds or until butter is melted.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir thoroughly.
Cook 30 more seconds or until thickened.
Microwave times may vary with different ovens.
My children prefer this recipe if I increase the sugar and decrease the cocoa a little.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place pecans and coconut in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour on top cake mix down center.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: liquid bubble bath
directions: Combine in jar all ingredients.
Mix well.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. (Spray dish with Pam first.)
Sprinkle cornflake crumbs over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lee brown's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil over medium heat, stirring continuously.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Mix the vanilla, eggs, baking soda and buttermilk and add to mixture.
Mix and pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: helen's salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O and let set to thicken.
Beat Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Add to Jell-O.
Fold in pineapple, mandarin oranges, nuts and cherries.

title: strawberry party cake
directions: Cut pound cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Crush 1 1/2 cups of berries.
Add sugar to cream cheese, beating until smooth. Fold in whipped topping and crushed berries.
Fill each layer with berry mix.
Frost cake with cream cheese mixture.
Garnish with berries and chill.

title: sweet potato praline souffle
directions: Mix and blend first 7 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mix brown sugar, flour and nuts together and spread on top of potato mixture.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Take the avocados and scrape them out with a spoon.
Set aside in a bowl.
Mix spices together.
Add to avocados along with lemon juice.
Serve with chips or anything else you want guacamole with.

title: russian tea cakes(pecan balls)
directions: Blend flour, butter and sugar. Add nuts and vanilla. Roll into balls the size of nuts. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Roll in powdered sugar. Cool. Roll in sugar again. Yields 4 dozen.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar until creamy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after
each addition.
Add flour and salt alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake in 325 degrees oven for 1 hour
and 15 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: microwave saucy baked eggs
directions: Lightly spray bottom and sides of 6-ounce custard cup with Pam. Place salsa in bottom. Break egg on top of sauce.

Prick yolk twice with sharp knife. Sprinkle salt and pepper over yolk. Top with olive oil and cheese. Cover loosely with paper toweling. Microwave on 100% power for 1 1/2 minutes or until desired texture.

title: chocolate cheese dessert
directions: Combine flour, pecans and butter in bowl; mix well.
Press into baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and whipped topping in mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Spread over baked crust.
Combine pudding mixes and milk in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Top with desired amount of additional whipped topping. Grate candy bar over top.
Chill until set.
(Bake crust at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Yields 20 servings.)

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend on low speed:
sugar, butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Slowly add flour mixture; will be fairly thick.
Add flavorings.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan, place layer of noodles, meat, cottage cheese and sauce.
Repeat layer.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions using the 3 cups of milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Layer bananas, cookies and pudding mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place roast in pressure cooker.
Cook for 2 hours at 15 pounds pressure.
Remove roast and tear into small pieces.
Remove all fat.
Combine all remaining ingredients for sauce.
Add meat to sauce and simmer 1 hour.
Yields 12 servings.

title: crock-pot ham and potatoes
directions: In crock-pot, alternate with all top 4 ingredients, 2 to 3 layers.
Top with can of soup (dab of milk).
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass jar.
(Use less oil and sugar for lower calorie dressing.)
Serve over finely grated cabbage and shredded with carrot, green pepper and onion, if desired.
Any leftover will keep a day or two in refrigerator.

title: fourteen carat cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add sugar, oil and eggs, mixing well.
Stir in carrots, drained pineapple and nuts.
Turn into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes, until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool a few minutes in pans; turn onto wire racks to cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Mix for 6 to 8 minutes. Small amounts may be mixed with colors for decorating.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Slowly add milk to avoid lumps. Add butter and vanilla.
Cook; stir constantly until mixture boils and begins to thicken.
(It will thicken some as it cools.)
Serve over unfrosted yellow sheet cake.

title: low-fat cabbage soup
directions: In oil, saute chopped onion and garlic, just until limp in a Dutch oven.
Add water and chicken cubes.
Add shredded cabbage and carrots; cook until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients; add more water, if needed.
Cook until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together in 9 x 13 dish.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, combine soup, garlic cheese and margarine and cook until all is melted.
Layer broccoli, soup mixture, Pepperidge Farm stuffing until all is used.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: hawaiian baked beans and franks
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine pineapple with remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet 'n sour tuna
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan except corn starch and tuna. Bring to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch made into a past with cold water.
Boil 1 minute.
Add tuna.
Heat to serving temperature. Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: poppy seed orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small mixing bowl, beat all ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin tins lined with paper liners or just greased.
Bake for 17 to 22 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 12 muffins.

title: 7 can soup(serves 8)
directions: Mix in Dutch oven. Simmer until hot, stirring occasionally.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and orange jello until thoroughly mixed.
Add 2 cans of mandarin oranges (drained) and stir until well blended into mixture.
Stir in miniature marshmallows.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Using scissors, snip bacon in small pieces into 2-quart casserole.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. With slotted spoon, remove bacon pieces to paper towel to drain. To bacon drippings, add sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until thick.
Add vegetables and onion.
Stir well; cover.
Microwave 6 minutes on High, stirring after 3 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving to blend.
Sprinkle bacon pieces on top.
This is even better reheated!

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all
together and put in baked pie shell or vanilla wafer pie crust.
Chill and serve at once.

title: walnut pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar in bowl.
Add oil, water and pumpkin; mix well.
Mix in flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in dates and walnuts.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
30 servings.

title: corn chip soup
directions: In a large pan, cook ground beef until browned; season with garlic salt.
Add onion and cook until limp or browned.
Add water, undrained beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add diced avocado.
Pass grated cheese, sour cream and corn chips for topping on each serving.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces.

title: cold vegetable dish
directions: Mix ingredients at least 8 hours before you need to serve. Serve cold.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Great for picnics or dinner parties.

title: sausage and cabbage
directions: Brown sausage in a jumbo (rectangular) electric skillet or Dutch oven.
Add 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in cabbage pieces and add additional water as needed to keep it moist.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender.
Cabbage will greatly shrink as it cooks.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: veggie squares
directions: Roll crescent rolls out on cookie sheet; bake as directed. Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing.
Spread on cooled crescent rolls.
Chop fine any or all of the veggies.
Press veggies into cream cheese mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix flours, baking powder and salt and set aside.
In mixer bowl, combine sugars, oil and eggs.
Beat.
Mix in rind and juice. Stir in flour mixture.
Do not beat.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: fried eggplant fingers
directions: Peel the eggplant and cut it into finger size strips.
Salt the eggplant generously.
This will be rinsed off later.
Let the salted eggplant set in a colander for about 20 minutes.
The salt helps pull the bitterness out of the eggplant.
Rinse well and wipe dry.
Place the flour into one bowl.

In another bowl, beat the eggs with the milk and Tabasco. Dip the eggplant into the flour, shaking off excess, and then into the egg mixture. Coat with the bread crumbs. Place on a rack so that the crumb coating will dry slightly.
Heat the oil to 375 degrees.
Fry the eggplant strips, turning as needed until delicately browned.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve with Carnival Dip (found in this section).

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Cook first 11 ingredients 1 minute.
Add shrimp or scallops and cook 2 minutes.
Add next 2 ingredients and cook 2 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Stir in beer and cook 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 2 (9-inch) deep dish pies.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until transparent. Mix other ingredients with onions. Put in casserole dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: june's turkey dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in 4 tablespoons butter in a large skillet until clear (do not brown).
Remove to mixing bowl.
In same skillet saute mushrooms and liver in 4 tablespoons butter. Add to mixing bowl.
Add onion and bread seasoning until all combined.
Pour 2 to 3 cups broth over mixture.
Bake at 325° in covered casserole.
Uncover last 30 minutes to brown top.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Have all ingredients measured and handy to mix.
Mix in order given.
Bake in oblong
greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) at 475° for 20 minutes.
Let sit a few minutes before cutting.

title: peppermints
directions: Mix together; form into small balls and then flatten with fork.
Let set in freezer until cold.
Then dip in melted chocolate.
Keep cool.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water (1 1/2 to 2 cups).
Add all ingredients.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw partially.
Take out of freezer at least 2 hours prior to serving.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 liter 7-Up.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Mix the eggplant, stuffing mix, egg, cheese, milk and onion; mix well together.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: peppermint ice cream dessert
directions: Combine crushed cookies with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with softened ice cream. Cover and freeze.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle meat on both sides with tenderizer.
Pierce deeply with fork.
Mix all other ingredients, except peppercorns; let stand for 2 to 3 hours (or overnight), turning every half hour. When ready to grill, pound in peppercorns.
Grill 15 minutes on each side.
Slice diagonally 1/2-inch thick.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip with or without lobster
directions: Cream cheeses, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add artichokes and lobster.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips or crusty bread.

title: minced clam casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in an uncovered casserole at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Remove chicken from bones.
Dilute cheese soup to a cream sauce.
Place ingredients in layers, ending with sauce. Sprinkle almonds.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook your onion and squash until tender.
Mix soup with pimento and all ingredients together.
Sprinkle your stuffing mix in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Place all ingredients in dish and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
The last 5 minutes, place grated cheese and rest of stuffing on top.
Heat until melted.

title: joe's peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend shortening with peanut butter (to make a softer cookie, add extra peanut butter) in mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Blend dry ingredients; mix.
Shape into balls.
Use 1 teaspoon for each.
Use ungreased pan.
Flatten with fork crisscross fashion.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until gold.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually add flour.
Mix well.
Chill dough.
Shape into balls or sticks.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all
ingredients
with
just
enough milk for stiff dough. Drop into deep fat until brown.

title: quick tomato rice soup
directions: Combine soup, broth, rice, celery, salt and pepper. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: grilled peanut butter sandwich
directions: Make nutty peanut butter sandwich.
Lightly spread outside sandwich with margarine or butter.
Pan-fry sandwich in frying pan until crisp on outside.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, pressing remainder firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Take chicken off bones. Make chicken gravy by putting chicken broth in a medium saucepan and heat to boiling.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute first 7 ingredients.
Add 1 can chicken broth.
Simmer until done.
In food processor, blend chicken mixture with mayo and cream cheese.
Line glass pan or baking dish with bacon strips.
Add chicken mixture and fold over bacon strips to cover. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all together, except peppers. Halve peppers and clean. Put meat mixture in each half and put in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (covered) and 10 minutes (uncovered).

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onions with margarine in saucepan over medium heat until tender, but not brown.
Stir occasionally.
Add precooked rice, salt, pepper and liquid.
Bring to a boil, uncovered.
Cover and simmer gently 3 minutes.
Add beans.
Serve with shredded cheese on top.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Spread soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 40
minutes. Sprinkle cheese over casserole and bake additional 5 minutes.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Brown chops in Crisco.
Mix all other ingredients in saucepan; simmer until thick.
Arrange chops in pan and pour mixture over chops.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onion, celery and pickle.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Cut squash in half. Remove seeds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until skin is tender. Remove strands with a fork.
Toss lightly with salt, pepper and butter.
Season with Parmesan or Italian seasoning or serve hot with spaghetti sauce for a delicious lo-cal spaghetti dinner.

title: chili dip
directions: Fry ground beef and green pepper.
Drain off grease.
Mix first seven ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 4 hours. Add on top 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese.

title: oven barbecue pork chops
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Salt and pepper both sides of pork chops.
Lay in baking dish.
Combine lemon juice, brown sugar, ketchup, water and Worcestershire sauce and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: instant biscuit rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and water-yeast mixture to flour mixture and mix well.
(Dough will probably be quite sticky.)
Dough may be covered in plastic wrap and refrigerated until ready to use or may be prepared for baking.

title: chili
directions: In Dutch oven or a large kettle, saute onion and green peppers in oil for 5 minutes or until soft.
Stir occasionally.
Add beef or turkey; cook slowly until lightly browned.
Stir often, breaking meat apart.
Add in tomato sauce and remaining seasonings.
Cook tightly covered over low heat for about 20 minutes.
Add beans; stir well.
Simmer uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or use for another favorite, chili dogs.

title: oatmeal softies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a bowl.
Cream butter and sugars in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in sifted ingredients, 1/3 at a time.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool cookies on baking sheet 1 minute.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Rub the mixing bowl with a piece of garlic.
Add cream cheese, milk, crab meat, lemon juice, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce. Combine all ingredients.

title: chocolate stuff
directions: Mix up pudding.
Blend in cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Garnish with crushed Oreo cookies.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn. Add beaten egg yolk.
Stir in pancake mix and fold in beaten egg white.
Slide by spoonful into hot oil to brown. Turn once.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add mushroom soup, broth, soy sauce, pepper sauce and pepper.
Add the chicken and simmer a few minutes.
Pour into 1-quart casserole; sprinkle with chow mein noodles and nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix well; brown in skillet.
Add to Dunky Sauce.

title: mother's buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little warm water.
Heat milk to melt shortening.
Add sugar and cool to lukewarm.
Warm water; add salt.
Combine all ingredients.
Add flour to make a non-sticky dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place.
Punch down and make into buns.
Let rise again and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes according to size of buns.

title: hungarian szekely gulyas
directions: Steam chopped pepper and onions for 15 minutes.
Add oil and meat and cook for 15 minutes longer.
Add salt, paprika, garlic and tomatoes.
Cook until meat is tender, approximately 1 hour. Simmer slowly for longer time to enhance flavors.
Drain sauerkraut before adding.
It may be rinsed, if desired, before adding.
Simmer for 15 to 25 minutes longer.
Top each serving with sour cream.
(This can be prepared in a crock-pot/slow cooker.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain well.
Let cool.
Saute chopped onion in oleo.
Add soup, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Start with a layer of potatoes then mushroom mix.
Add cheese slices; repeat in layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place diced rhubarb in greased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Sprinkle with sugar.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour over rhubarb.
Sprinkle with dry Jell-O.
Pour boiling water over Jell-O.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water and mash.
Mix together all ingredients except milk.
Heat milk to boiling point.
Add mixture.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes in deep dish.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat milk and eggs together.
Then add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat a little again and bake in unbaked pie shell.
Is good plain or put berries or peaches or coconut (1/2 cup) in.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Rinse and drain macaroni.
Put in bowl.
Drain tuna, then mix all of the ingredients with tuna and macaroni.
Chill and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix all together well. Warm in oven at 350° until warm through. Spread on crackers.

title: mee mom's irish potato candy
directions: Melt butter in top of a double boiler; add water and vanilla. Pour butter mixture over sugar and combine well with your hands. Work in coconut.
Pinch off small pieces of mixture and shape into balls.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and roll each piece in cinnamon.
Refrigerate again.

title: low-fat chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and top with 10 ready to bake canned biscuits (look for lowest in fat grams).
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and flatten them.
Cook until biscuits are brown at 350°.
May double recipe.

title: pineapple sauce for ham
directions: Heat all ingredients together and serve over ham.

title: children's play dough
directions: Mix flour
and salt together.
Add oil and water gradually. Knead
until
the mixture is smooth and easy to handle. Add more flour
as needed.
To color, knead in food coloring. To store, place in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Put flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar in large bowl. Cut in Crisco.
Blend in measuring cup eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk to dry mix.
Add more flour if needed to make nice dough.
Roll out on floured board to 1/16 inch thickness. Cut out shapes; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Remove, cool and ice.
These store well.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and cut up.
Brown hamburg and onion.
Mix bacon, hamburg, onion, beans, sugar, ketchup and salt.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or slow in crock-pot.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger in small amount of oil.
Add onions.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer very slowly for 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
May be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well, and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered. Spoon onto buns.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal, butter and boiling water in saucepan.
Cover. Remove from heat.
Let set 20 minutes.
Add sugars and eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add to the oatmeal mixture.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Then cook with diced onion until soft with beans barely covered with water.
Do not drain.
Mix with ketchup, syrup, salt and pepper and put into a casserole dish. Fry chops until pink and slightly brown.
Push these to the bottom of the casserole dish and place bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pot o' gold soda bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mix resembles coarse meal. Stir in fruit bits.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined. Turn dough out onto floured surface.
Knead gently 1 minute.
Form dough into a 6-inch ball.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly so that center mounds and outer edge of ball is about 1 1/2-inches high.
With a sharp knife, cut a cross 1/2-inch deep in top of bread, or score into wedges.
Bake at 350° above oven center 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 round loaf.
Serves 8.
Preparation Time:

title: love light yellow chiffon cake
directions: Heat
oven
Grease well and flour pan.
Beat egg whites
until
frothy.
Gradually
beat in 1/2 cup sugar, continue beating until very stiff and glossy.
Sift remaining sugar, flour,
baking powder and salt into another bowl.
Add oil, half of the milk and flavoring.	Beat 1 minute on medium mixer speed or	150
strokes by hand.
Add remaining milk and egg.
Beat one more minute.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in greased oblong pan at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: my mother-in-law's stroganoff
directions: Dip beef in flour.
Saute in onions and mushrooms until brown. Add 1 can beef consomme and wine.
Simmer until tender.
Add sour cream.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream.
Cook over low heat.
Stir until soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Stir until
only
medium
warm.	Add pecans. Stir well coating each pecan
half.
Place
pecans
individually on waxed paper. Yield: 6 cups.

title: potato salad
directions: *Can substitute chopped celery and salt.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water; drain and rinse.
Pour water on beans until just covered.
Add salt pork.
Bring to a boil and then let simmer until beans are tender.
Add sugar and bake in oven at 350° until they start to thicken, about an hour; or, you can cook in crock-pot all day.
Add sugar about half way through the day.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, milk and vegetables.
Over medium heat, heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese until cheese is melted.

title: favorite punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Mix frozen lemonade according to directions on can and add to Jell-O mixture. Add pineapple juice. Stir thoroughly. Chill. Pour over ice in punch bowl.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream sugar and butter; mix in flour and salt.
Press 3/4 of mixture into 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Warm jam slightly in microwave; spread over base. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top.
Bake for 40 minutes. Makes 24 bars.

title: egg and sausage souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 12 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan. Serves 6 to 10.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, butter, egg and milk; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch deep dish or regular pie pan.
Lay peach slices over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cupful of sugar and 3 tablespoons of peach juice. Beat for 2 minutes.
Spread evenly over top of cake, leaving 1 inch around edge.
Combine 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: best biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pan.
Mix batter.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Place in pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: red cabbage and apples
directions: In skillet, heat bacon drippings.
Blend brown sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Insert whole cloves into onion and add with shredded cabbage and sliced apples to skillet.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cover and stir until cabbage is tender, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mock duck(filled steak)
directions: To make dressing, beat eggs; add milk.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Add the onion and seasoning.
Work butter into mixture, mixing thoroughly.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Spray a
9 x l3 pan with cooking spray.
Combine dry cake mix, 2 beaten eggs and oleo.
Spread this mixture into the pan. Sprinkle pecans, coconut and chocolate chips on top of crust.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar.
Pour on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 mins.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Mix with wooden spoon, then work with your hands.
Wrap with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out a section at
time, 1/8-inch thick, on a floured board.
Cut into squares 2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Fill with filling in center of square.
Fold over and seal lightly, like a small turnover.
Bake at 350° on a greased cookie sheet 12 minutes or until light brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after cooled.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen cookies.
Can be made large, if desired.
Any flavor Baker's cookie filling can be used.

title: spaghetti a la carbonara
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Meanwhile, dice and cook bacon until almost crisp.
Remove from pan and reserve.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings from skillet.
Add butter or margarine, garlic and onion to pan and cook over low heat until onion is soft but not brown.
Discard garlic clove.
Put hot spaghetti in large bowl.
Add eggs, parsley, cheese and pepper and stir until well mixed.
Add cooked onion with pan drippings and bacon pieces. Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and orange rind.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts.
Combine milk, eggs and melted butter.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and pour in milk mixture.
Mix gently, only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 55 to 60 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Either cook and cool peas or empty the box of frozen peas onto a towel to absorb moisture as they defrost.
Mix tuna, celery, onion and water chestnuts to mayonnaise, along with thawed peas.
(Peas should be thawed some to avoid excess water in the finished salad.)

title: apple nut muffins
directions: Grease or line 12 muffin cups.
In a bowl, beat egg with juice, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, sugars, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in nuts and apple.
Fill prepared muffin cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: cut glass salad
directions: Mix jello in separate oblong baking dishes.
Only mix hot water as directed on package
and set in fridge.
When set, cut in 1/2-inch squares.

title: scripture cake
directions: After following instructions in Proverbs 23:14, pour batter into well-greased loaf pans and bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Cool and slice after a few of John 11:9.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine or butter; set aside to cool.
Mix eggs and sugar; add margarine or butter.
Add flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat on medium with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 slightly thawed pie shells.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower.
Cut flowerets into bite size pieces.
Layer lettuce, onion, cauliflower and bacon in a 3-quart bowl. Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Mix well. Spread evenly over top, sealing to edge of bowl. Sprinkle with cheese, chopped lettuce and onion. Cover salad tightly and refrigerate 24 hours. Toss gently before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: blonde brownies
directions: To sifted flour add baking powder, soda, salt and nuts. To melted shortening add, 1 T. water and sugar-cool. Add egg and vanilla to sugar mixture and stir. Stir in flour mixture gradually. Spread in greased 8x8 pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake in oven 20-25 minutes (do not over bake unless you want bricks). Cool in pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers with melted butter and x sugar.
Set aside. Whip the cream cheese, 1 cup of sugar and vanilla.
Whip the cream or Milnot and mix with cheese.
Add pineapple and the jello.
(If you use pineapple jello, leave pineapple out.)
Pour into crust.

title: sugar marbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Cream the margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Slowly mix in dry ingredients. Divide dough in half.
Into half, mix the melted unsweetened chocolate.
Pinch off about 1/2 teaspoon each plain and chocolate dough.
Roll together to achieve a marble effect. Roll in sugar.
Space 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets and bake about 10 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Drain grease from ground beef.
Put in crock pot; add cheese, picante sauce and soup. Simmer in crock pot until cheese has melted, stirring occasionally. Serve with Tostado chips.

title: deer jerky
directions: Soak meat in sauce overnight.
Cut meat into lean, 3/8-inch wide strips, 6 inches long.
Remove all fat so it will not turn rancid.
Cut meat with the grain.
Soak all night.
Salt and pepper one side only.
Place toothpick through end of strip and hang from top oven rack with foil on bottom rack.
Set oven at lowest setting.
Leave door ajar to let moisture out.
Leave meat in 10 to 12 hours, until meat is dark and no moisture.

title: rice pudding with cardamom(indian recipe)
directions: In heavy-bottomed pot, add rice and milk.
Cook at medium heat until rice is tender (may need to add more milk, as needed, until rice is done).
Stir occasionally.
When done, add sugar, raisins and almonds.
Stir well.
When mixture is cooled, add ground cardamom and the rose essence.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook pepper, onion and garlic in butter.
Add tomatoes.
Cook spaghetti.
Add sauce and boned chicken to spaghetti.
Cook 1 hour.
About 10 to 15 minutes before serving, add the mushrooms, pimientos and cheese.

title: very tasty fruit salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and stir well.
Store in refrigerator until chilled, about 2 to 3 hours.

title: gardenburgers(vegetarian)
directions: Pour onion in a 3 qt. saucepan with vegetable stock and bring to a boil. Add bulgur, chickpeas, salt and vegetables; stir until combined. Turn off heat, cover and let stand 15 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed. Remove pot from heat. Using a potato masher, mash ingredients together, making sure all chickpeas get mashed. Form into four patties. Lightly coat a 10 inch nonstick pan with cooking spray and turn heat to medium. Place burgers in pan when hot and cook 2-3 minutes per side or until heated through and golden.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Prepare rice and set aside.
Prepare vegetable medley according to package directions. Set aside.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Stir in 3/4 cup cornmeal.
Cut in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Combine 1 slightly beaten egg with 3/4 cup milk and stir into the cornmeal mixture until blended.
Insert wooden skewers into the ends of the franks and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and place in saucepan with chopped onion.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Combine bacon, cheese, egg and marjoram; add to mashed squash.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat egg; add milk.
Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Pour batter into large funnel, holding finger over bottom.
Allow batter to run out of funnel into 375° deep fat.
Make swirls as dough runs out, beginning small and increasing to about 7 inches in diameter.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn once; drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and butter together slightly.
Add buttermilk with soda.
Cook to hard ball stage, stirring constantly.
Take from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until cool and thick enough to drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper.
Add nuts before dropping.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery until tender.
Add ground beef and Italian style tomatoes.
Cook at 375° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: disappearing butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Melt together butterscotch chips and margarine.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Put into pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients. Stir into that the next 4 ingredients. Add to that the remaining ingredients. You may need to mix this with your hands. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter in heavy saucepan; stir.
Add powdered sugar gradually.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.

title: bacon wrapped chestnuts
directions: Soak water chestnuts in soy sauce overnight.
Drain.
Toss in brown sugar until coated.
Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around chestnut.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and crisp.

title: fudgy scotch squares
directions: Butter 2 pans (square 9-inch).
Mix above together with spoon. Press into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 45 minutes before cutting.

title: chuck wagon casserole
directions: Saute onion and meat; add chili powder (to taste).
Spray casserole dish with Pam. Layer noodles, creamed corn, meat mixture and tamales (sliced).
Pour thinned tomato sauce over top, then repeat.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased-only Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and salt in double boiler; add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring constantly.
Then add milk.

title: pfeffernuse cookies(german christmas cookies)
directions: Bring to a boil and cook only to melt sugar before pouring while hot over cookies, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: mushrooms (stuffed)
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems from caps.
Brush caps with some oil and place in a baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
In skillet cook bacon (or sausage) until no longer pink; remove from heat. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Add bread crumbs and chopped stems.
Spoon crumb mixture into oiled mushroom caps. Pour water in bottom of baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sandra's frosty
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.
Push the blend button for 5 seconds.
Pour frosty into cup and serve.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Shake chicken in flour and fry until golden brown.
Place chicken to one side and add onions, green pepper and garlic; brown lightly.
Combine tomatoes, etc. Add to chicken and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until tender (covered).
Serve with noodles.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Slice potatoes round ways, then place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour on ground beef and onions.

title: simple salmon salad
directions: Drain fish and break into large pieces.
Combine all ingredients, except salad greens.
Toss lightly and chill.
Serve on salad greens.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put uncooked rice in casserole dish.
Pour chicken broth over rice (wet all rice).
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour can of soup over ingredients.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on the mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours (cover during first hour).
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar and let stand 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Mix Sure-Jell and water and boil 1 minute.
Pour over strawberries; mix well 2 minutes.
Put in containers.
Let stand 24 hours, then freeze.

title: hawaiian chicken breast
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in 2-quart microwave dish.
Microwave on full power for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: shrimp in lobster sauce
directions: It's easier if you combine some of the ingredients because you need to cook on medium-high and you will not have time to remember what goes next.

title: scotch mutton broth
directions: Soak the pearl barley overnight in cold water.
Cut the lamb into piece, removing as much fat as possible.
Put into a soup kettle with water and salt and bring slowly to a boil, skimming it well.
Add the soaked pearl barley and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat, then add other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour. Serve with tortilla chips and grated cheese.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Make a pie crust out of cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 minutes.
Saute onions in oil and put in pie shell.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Top with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Wonderful pie!

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and lemon juice in large bowl.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Add nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake for 6 to 7 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Honey-Butter Whip:
Combine and cream together 1/4 pound butter and 1/2 cup honey.
Add 1/2 cup whipping cream.
Whip until fluffy.

title: raspberry-applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add raspberries and applesauce.
Pour into greased mold.
Set in refrigerator.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In skillet, heat meat and onion until onion is tender.
In bowl combine meat mixture, red pepper and cumin.
Set aside.
In same skillet, combine soup and milk.
Combine sour cream and flour; stir into sauce mixture.
Cook until bubbly.
Stir in 1/3 cup of sauce into meat mixture.
Stir corn into remaining sauce.
Fill each tortilla with 1/4 cup meat mixture.
Roll up and place in sauce in skillet.
Spoon some sauce over tortillas.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, serve.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Boil tomatoes for 10 minutes with sugar.
Add jello.
Simmer slowly 20 minutes more.
Seal in jars and refrigerate.
Makes 3 small jelly jars.

title: oriental rice
directions: Dissolve
bouillon
cubes
in
ounces
of hot water. Brown rice in 1 1/2 sticks of margarine.
Add bouillon and all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in buttered casserole.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and orange juice in small pan.
Add butter and cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Pour over sweet potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese; stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with French bread slices.

title: noodle hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add pepper, liquids and uncooked noodles.
Season to taste.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In nonstick pan, brown onion and saute mushrooms.
Brown ground beef, adding garlic to taste.
Add olives, salsa and stewed tomatoes.
Let cook until you feel flavors are well blended.
In oblong pan, place one layer of tortillas; top with meat mixture and cheese.
Keep repeating until pan is full.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with tossed salad.

title: pizza dessert
directions: Roll out cookie dough and press into a pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit in circular design over filling.
Prepare glaze and pour over fruit.
Chill.

title: low-fat cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Spray 2-quart round casserole with nonstick coating.
Place cream cheese in the casserole.
Stir in the milk.
Stir in the soup until well blended, then add the thawed vegetables, cooked chicken, uncooked rice, half the Parmesan cheese, pepper and garlic powder.
tags: low-fat condensed cream of chicken soup

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes (not too thin).
Soak overnight in lime water. Make sure tomatoes are covered with water.
Drain and wash very carefully.
Soak 5 hours in cold water, changing every 1/2 hour. Make syrup of sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to rolling boil and add tomatoes.
Let stand 12 hours in syrup.
Bring syrup and tomatoes to rolling boil and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: spicy pumpkin bread
directions: Beat pumpkin, oil and cold water into eggs.
Mix well and then add dry ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip and nut cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add flour, chips and nuts.
Dough should be real stiff.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° to 400°.

title: grandma stillson's zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 2 greased pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, milk and butter.
Add baking powder, berries and flour until dough hangs from spoon. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 36 large muffins.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients and hot milk.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: creamed corn
directions: Mix cheese, milk and chives in a
saucepan
until cheese melts.
Drain the corn and heat in the
cheese mixture.
Serves 4.

title: tuna stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut a thin slice from one side of each potato, scoop out the interior.
Place in bowl.
Mash, adding the hot milk.
Whip until fluffy.
Add green onions, egg and butter, whipping mixture well.
Season with salt and cayenne pepper.
Fold in tomato and tuna.
Pile this mixture into potato skins, mounding 1 teaspoon high.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place into baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes until potatoes are heated. Yields 4 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine hard-boiled eggs, potatoes and onion in bowl.
In separate bowl, combine oil, vinegar and salt.
Pour mixture over potato mixture.
Chill for at least 2 hours (can chill overnight). Before serving, add mayonnaise to taste.

title: congo squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: chicken wing-ding spice sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, pour entire bottle of barbecue sauce. Add chili powder and black pepper.
Also add cayenne pepper, Texas Pete hot sauce and brown sugar.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken wings or leg quarters; place in oven.

title: creamy rice bake casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and paprika in large bowl.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can add leftover chopped chicken, turkey or ham if desired.

title: celery casserole
directions: Parboil sliced celery, onions (sliced) and salt combined. Drain well.
Mix soup, cornstarch, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Add to celery mixture.
Place in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all together. Chill and serve.

title: gringo chicken mole
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water.
When tender remove the bones and fat.
Place in blender approximately 3 cups of the warm chicken broth.
Add the chili seasoning, minced garlic, cocoa, peanut butter and flour, blending until smooth.
Slowly add the flour mixture, stirring constantly to boiling chicken broth. Taste.
If not to your liking, add some more chili powder.
Now add the deboned chicken.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry delight
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add (blended) strawberries and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add bananas. Pour into a 9x13-inch pan.
Keep frozen.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with fish or French fries.
Yields 1 3/4 quarts.

title: white chili
directions: Cover chicken with water and season to taste (salt, pepper, all seasoning salt).
Cook for about 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: To egg nog, add flavoring and powdered coffee.
Stir well until blended.
Top with (drop by spoonfuls) vanilla ice cream which has been softened slightly and whipping cream (whipped). Let these float on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: strawberry chantilly
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare pastry for two-crust pie as directed on package.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Roll each into 7-inch circles.
Trim edge evenly and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick circle thoroughly; sprinkle each with granulated sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Reserve 3 strawberries for garnish.
Chop remaining berries.
In chilled bowl, beat cream, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Fold in chopped berries.
Stack circles, spreading about 3/4 cup cream mixture between each.
Frost top with remaining cream mixture.
Garnish with reserved berries.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 8.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours in tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured.

title: yum yum sweet potatoes
directions: Place in ovenproof dish.

title: pie crust
directions: Break egg into a bowl.
Add vinegar and water.
Beat well. Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add the egg mixture and stir to form a ball.
This makes 4 crusts.

title: fig preserves cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil and beat well.
Add eggs, then buttermilk gradually.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: amount needed to make 500 chili buns
directions: Brown ground meat with garlic and onion (cut up). Add tomato paste, chili powder, salt and pepper (to taste).
Simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: bride's pie crust(one crust)
directions: Mix all together until like fine meal.
Add 4 tablespoons cold water; mix and roll out.

title: fresh kosher style dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumber.
Make brine of vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to boil.
Place in layer of dill, garlic slices and mustard seed in the bottom of each jar.
Packing cucumbers in jar.
When jar is half filled add more dill.
Pour hot brine over cucumbers.
Seal them.
Hot bath for 5 minutes.

title: 6 layer dessert
directions: Pour cherries over bottom of pan; pour pineapple over this. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts over cake. Sprinkle coconut over nuts.
Drizzle melted oleo over coconut. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Place lentils in a bowl and cover with water.
Saute garlic, celery and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in carrot and potatoes.
Drain water from lentils and add lentils to vegetables. Add water, tomato juice, salt, thyme and brown rice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Add corn and cook 20 minutes more.

title: oh-so-easy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of the M&M's candies.
Spread the mixture in the pan and sprinkle the reserved candies on top.
Bake about 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: dijon-honey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in fridge.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Lower heat and add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve hot.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain fruits and reserve juices.
Put juices, drained from the fruit, in a saucepan.
Add lemon juice and cinnamon stick to juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add drained fruit and orange sections and heat through.
Serve hot or chilled. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresno chicken breast ole
directions: Remove skin and bone chicken. Pound between wax paper to 1/4-inch. Drain chiles and olives. Combine with cheese and onion. Divide into 6 equal portions.
Sprinkle one portion down center of each breast.
Roll chicken around filling.
Fold in ends.
Secure with toothpicks, if necessary.
Combine butter, chili powder and cumin. Coat rolls in butter mix.

Roll in crushed tortilla chips. Arrange chicken rolls, seam side down, in shallow greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve with topping of sour cream and taco sauce. Guacamole or cubed avocado is optional.

title: glorified chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soup, pepper and thyme. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 35 minutes, or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in foil; bake for 1 hour at 400°.
Debone and cut into large, thick pieces.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips. Mix the soups and milk; set aside.
Butter a large casserole; lightly sprinkle a little water on the bottom.
Layer ingredients as follows:
tortillas (solidly arranged), then chicken, peppers, onion, cheese and a little of the soup.
Repeat layering, being sure not to have chicken on the bottom or the top.
Let stand in the refrigerator 24 hours to blend flavors.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: banana split
directions: Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs and pat into bottom of 9x13 pan.
Beat eggs on high 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, softened butter, vanilla and beat for 5 minutes.
Spread over crumb layer and chill for 30 minutes.
Top with pineapple and bananas; cover with Cool Whip and top with cherries.

title: aunt georgia's zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Boil all vegetables in the water until tender.
Add the tomato paste, barbecue sauce and liquid smoke.
Simmer slowly for about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator in jar until ready for use.
(Oh yes!
The sauce must be strained before storing!)
Try it on beef ribs, chicken or pork ribs.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; add water, tomatoes, taco seasoning and beans. Heat and serve with your choice of avocados, corn chips, cheese, onions or sour cream.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, walnuts and lemon juice; place on the bottom of a loaf pan.
Beat cream; add confectioners sugar and pineapple.
Spread on top of cranberry mixture.
Freeze.
Slice to serve.

title: southern style hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger in shortening.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Simmer until tender.
Add other ingredients and slowly cook for 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pigs in a poke
directions: Mix all together and let sit for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 475°. Arrange 1 pound of sausage links in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Brown sausage for 10 minutes in oven.
Pour batter over sausage.
Bake for 10 minutes at 475°.
Reduce to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until raised.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and beat 3 minutes (medium speed).
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until cake springs up when lightly touched.

title: sauce for pork
directions: Mix all together and bring to a good boil.

title: killer tomato sauce(to go with "lasagne to die for" or spaghetti of course.)
directions: Saute carrots, celery, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until lightly colored.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Makes 5 cups.

title: ranch salad
directions: Mix dressing mix with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as directed.
Mix powdered sugar and lemonade.
