When cake is done, remove from oven and poke holes in it with fork.
Pour lemonade mix over cake.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: lemon butter chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to a one-quarter to one-eighth-inch thickness.

Combine flour and salt; dredge chicken in mixture. Liberally sprinkle lemon pepper on each side of chicken breasts. Saute chicken in melted butter for about five minutes per side or until lightly browned.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute the ham and onions in a large pot over medium heat until the onions are tender but not brown.
Add potatoes and water; cook until potatoes are done.
Add fish and cook until the fish may be separated in large pieces with a fork.
Add milk and seasonings. (For a richer soup, substitute 1 cup of cream for 1 cup of the milk.)
Garnish with finely minced parsley.

title: layered salad
directions: Fry, drain and crumble bacon.
Wash and tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Cut cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Place ingredients in layers beginning with lettuce.
Do not toss.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Toss to serve.
Do not cut lettuce or it will turn brown.

title: scallops milano
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place undrained scallops in a single layer in shallow baking dish. Add wine so liquid covers 2/3 up the scallops. Sprinkle with garlic powder, onion powder and parsley flakes. Mix melted butter with cracker crumbs and cover scallops. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the crumbs and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tossed greek salad
directions: Break lettuce and spinach into small pieces and toss with next 7 ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste and toss again.
Sprinkle Feta cheese over top.
Just before serving, pour even amounts of olive oil and vinegar over salad and toss at table.
May sprinkle anchovies on top also if desired.
Serve with hard bread, crackers or crusty rolls.
This salad is also good with vinaigrette dressing.

title: christmas cake
directions: Beat eggs
well.
Add
sugar and continue beating until well mixed.
Add
vanilla
and almond flavoring. Sift together flour, baking
powder
and
salt.	Set aside.
Combine pecans, cherries, pineapple
and
dates.
Sift flour mixture over this and mix well, then add eggs and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly.	Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake over a pan of water for 1 1/2
hours	in
a 250° oven.
Serve when cool. Like a fruit cake, portions should be kept small.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Mix in ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and drained beans.
Mix with ground beef; top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook in crock-pot.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add salad oil, eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add carrots and pecans. Bake in 3 layers in cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: garlic basil green beans
directions: Rinse and trim beans.
Steam until crisp-tender, 7 to 8 minutes.
While beans cook, combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes until thickened.
Or, combine in a glass dish and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring at 30 second intervals.
Arrange beans in a serving dish.
Pour sauce over beans.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Place sliced sharp cheese on each muffin half.
Spread chili sauce on each muffin.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Add desired topping.
Place on paper plate and microwave 2 minutes on High.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Melt margarine in another pan. Blend in flour and salt. Gradually add milk and cheese. Drain potatoes.
Pour in baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pudding dessert
directions: In bowl, cut margarine into the flour until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes. Cool.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar till smooth. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
In small mixer bowl, beat pudding and milk on low speed 2 minutes.
Carefully spread over the cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Yield 12 to 16 servings.

title: aunt viddie's onion supper
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onions and cook, covered, until tender. Combine soup and milk; pour over onions.
Add Cheddar cheese. Heat until smooth and bubbles.
Serve over toast.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in water, catsup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff rice with fork and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand for 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve as a main dish with salad.
Serves 4.

title: olallaberry buckwheat pancakes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in buttermilk, oil and egg yolks.
Using electric mixer, beat egg whites in medium bowl until peaks form.
Gently fold whites into batter.
Heat large skillet over medium-high heat.
Brush skillet with melted butter.
Drop batter into skillet to make desired size pancakes.
Sprinkle a handful of berries on top of batter.
Cook until tops are covered with small bubbles and bottoms are brown. Flip and cook until golden, about 1 minute.
Repeat with remaining batter and berries.
Serve with berry syrup.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all together; form into a ball and roll ball until covered with pecan pieces. Serve with cinnamon-graham crackers. Mmm good.

title: pastitsio(home-style casserole from greece)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Cover bottom of 13x9x2-inch pan or pyrex dish with graham cracker crumbs, reserving some for top.
Combine beaten eggs, sugar and melted butter in a saucepan.
Cook until thick and smooth. Cool; stir in vanilla.
Pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle with pecans, then spread on 1 c. whipped cream.
Spoon strawberries over cream. Spread remaining cup of whipped cream over berries.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Cover and freeze.
Set out 1 hour before serving.

title: pineapple and banana cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl (make a hole in the center).
Pour in all other ingredients.
Stir with a spoon. Do not overbeat.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: delicious chocolate pudding
directions: Bake brownie mix and cool thoroughly.
Follow directions to make chocolate pudding.
Beginning with brownie, layer chocolate pudding, Cool Whip and crushed Butterfinger bars.
Make 3 to 4 layers, depending on size of bowl, ending with crushed candy on top.
Refrigerate.

title: deviled scallops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil scallops in water 3 minutes; drain. In saucepan, combine butter, flour, mustard, salt and pepper. Slowly stir in milk; cook over low heat just until thickened.
Add scallops.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with combined crumbs and butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and pepper.
Mix together with beans, tomato sauce, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: candied pumpkin dandies
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients on medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes or microwave for 7 minutes.
Turn into buttered pan.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cool completely.
Butter hands.
Shape into balls. Roll in chopped nuts.
Top each with 1/2 candy cherry.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy chicken delight
directions: Beat eggs with fork; add all but chicken at first.
Mix well. Add chicken and place in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Then take one package of stuffing mix, follow directions on package.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 20 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: pork chops and cheese casserole
directions: Spray Pam in the bottom of a medium size casserole dish.
Put in a layer of chops (about 4).
Place in a layer of potatoes, then a layer of onion.
Repeat layers. Top with a layer of cheese slices.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and chops are done.
May vary amounts to suit the size of family.

title: stage planks
directions: Cream butter, sugar and molasses.
Add lemon flavoring to buttermilk.
Sift flour, salt, spices and soda together.
Add alternately with the buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend together well.
Chill for several hours.
Turn out onto a floured board; roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 2-inch strips. Place on greased baking sheets; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan or casserole dish.
Blend sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread over noodles.
Saute beef, onions, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add tomato sauce to beef mixture; heat through.
Pour over cream cheese and noodles.
Stick a fork down through noodles so tomato mixture will go through.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: nut bars(croation)
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until light.
Add the ground nuts and mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Do not mix long after egg whites are added.
Take small amounts of dough and shape into balls.
Roll in coarse sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: jiffy cheese cake cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cupcake pan with liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer on bottom of each liner.

title: five layer butter pecan cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on cake box except add 1 extra egg and use milk in place of water.
Make 5 thin layers in 8-inch cake pans.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: micro-magic fudge
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, margarine, salt and milk in large mixing bowl.
microwave on high for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir well, mixing in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered dish.
Chill 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: clam dip
directions: Put cream cheese in small mixing bowl and soften.
Add catsup and onion and mix well.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Mix.
Add drained clams and mix.
Chill.
Serve with crackers, chips or fresh vegetables.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp well.
Blend softened cream cheese with lemon juice, then add sour cream and dressing.
Mix and blend well. Then add shrimp and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Cut fruit in bite size pieces for dipping.
Mix ingredients for dip.
Add lemon juice to taste.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Add onion, baking powder, salt, eggs and enough flour to make a batter stiff enough to drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning just once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix baking mix and granulated sugar.
Beat in milk until smooth.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan. Top with apples. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
Pour boiling water over apples. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm with sweetened whipped cream. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and baking powder. Gradually add milk and flour.
Dough will be very thick; set aside.
Make Cheese Filling.

title: fruit vinegar
directions: Combine fruit and vinegar in a sterilized glass jar with airtight seal.
Leave in warm place to steep.
Shake jar occasionally.
Strain fruit and vinegar into saucepan, pressing to extract flavor from fruit.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and stir to blend.
Place mixture over low heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Transfer to sterilized jars.
For a more attractive presentation, add a few fresh berries or pieces of fruit.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cut rolls into half.
Mix pudding, sugar, cinnamon, pecans.
Put part of mixture on bottom of pan, top with rolls.
Pour remaining mixture over rolls.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Let set overnight.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in tube pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix flavor packet from noodles with oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper.

title: quaker vanishing oatmeal rising cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in molasses, water, flour, salt, soda, ginger, nutmeg and allspice.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: eagle brand fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips, stirring a few times in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Makes about 2 pounds of candy.

title: cool whip cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned (15 to 20 minutes).

title: chocolate cake roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray jelly pan with Pam.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar at high speed until foamy.
Sprinkle Sugar Twin over and beat until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.
Beat yolks 5 minutes until thick and lemon colored.
Blend in milk and flavorings, then add dry ingredients, mixing at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium, scraping sides occasionally. Pour yolk mixture over whites and with rubber spatula, carefully fold by hand until evenly blended.
Pour into pan and bake 7 minutes until done.
Allow to set 1 minute; loosen around edges and invert onto clean towel.
Roll with towel from narrow end, leaving open side on bottom.
Cool completely on wire rack. Unroll; spread cake with whipped frosting to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Roll cake with frosting.
Chill until serving time.

title: bear paws (modern)(bella coola tribe)
directions: Marinate paws in vinegar and myrtle leaves for 5 days.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk a little at a time until ingredients are mixed well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixture and then add butter; cook until thick.
Pour in 9-inch cooked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and add 8 teaspoons sugar and put on top of pie.
Put in oven until brown.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, meat, onion and sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle cheese and paprika. Bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are done.
Makes 6 servings; 273 calories each serving, 2 medium fat meat and 1 1/2 bread exchanges.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion and ground beef. Add molasses, catsup, dry mustard and salt. Cook 2 hours in crock-pot or 30 minutes in oven.

title: calico beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and brown.
Add onion and brown.
Add ground round and brown.
When all is browned, add catsup, brown sugar and vinegar.
Add all beans and place in large baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° until pie shell is golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, grated rind and nutmeg.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs and milk.
Blend well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Decorate with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: toasty peach crisp
directions: Put peaches with juice in 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: rocky road cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool

title: amaretto fruit dip
directions: Mix together; add Amaretto to taste.
Serve with favorite fruits.
Top with almonds.
Low-fat substitutions work great.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all together and pour over one large cut up chicken in Tupperware container.
Let meat marinate at least 24 hours.
Grill on the grill or in oven.
Delicious!

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix and serve in place of potato salad.
You may add boiled eggs, pickles, sweet relish, pimentos or anything you like which goes into potato salad.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt Hershey bar in double boiler; cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, soda and milk and mix.
Add flour, syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour in Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix meat and other ingredients together and shape it round to fit your crock-pot.
Put potatoes around meat loaf, peeled or not. If potatoes are peeled, wrap in foil.
Cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: slow cooked pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into 1 inch strips.
Brown in oil in deep skillet.
Add 1 large onion.
Put in pre-heated crockpot.
Slice 2 large green peppers in strips.
Set aside.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and salt; measure and add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Form into crescents about the size of your middle finger or smaller.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
When hot, roll in confectioners sugar and after cool, roll in sugar again.

title: barberton fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half lengthwise; separate thighs from legs The chicken pieces should be all about the same size for even cooking.

title: grandma's toffee squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and flour.
Spread thinly on 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Place broken chocolate on warm cookie and spread when soft.
Sprinkle with nuts and cut into squares while still warm.
Easy and delicious!

title: "poor man's cookies"
directions: Combine oats, sugars and flour; set aside.
Combine soda and water; stir into oats mixture, along with shortening and vanilla. Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Top with Ritz crackers, then top with butter.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form mixture into a "crust" in a 10-inch pie plate.

title: linguine salad
directions: Boil linguine and drain.
Add the remaining ingredients and toss.
You may add black olives and cheese if you prefer.

title: rolled oat stoakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and, if too dry, add water to form patties. Brown lightly in oil.
Drop into boiling broth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender; salt well.
Boil rice until fluffy.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave for 1 minute.
When finished, mix everything together, including the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil
chicken until tender.
Remove and debone chicken. Combine
flour, salt, shortening and milk.	Roll out dumplings on floured
surface.
Add
broth
as needed.
Add chicken and drop dumplings into broth.
Cook as needed.
Time of preparation: 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Let cool and remove from bone.
Add chicken, onions and celery in large pan or casserole dish.
Add all soups and boiled noodles.
Stir up all ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top covering dish completely.
Bake, covered, for about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serve.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Season with salt and crushed red pepper.
Mix enchilada sauce per package instructions.
Boil large pasta shells until cooked.
Drain shells.
Fill with ground beef.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add chopped onion; cook until tender.
Add flour; whisk.
Cook 1 minute on low heat, stirring. Add milk and chicken broth; cook on medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Add cheese and seasonings, stirring until cheese has melted.
Add broccoli; reduce heat and cook until broccoli is tender (about 30 minutes).
Do not boil.

title: meat stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook the cabbage in boiling water to cover for a few minutes until wilted.
Drain.
Mix 2 tablespoons soup with remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Divide meat mixture evenly among cabbage leaves.
Starting at stem end, roll up and fold in edges. Pin leaves with wooden toothpicks.
Place rolls in skillet, seam side down, and pour remaining soup over them.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 40 minutes or until fork-tender. Stir now and then and spoon sauce over rolls.
Makes 8 servings.

title: family day punch
directions: Freeze in ice cream pail.
Thaw to slush (about 5 hours).
Add 3 quarts diet Seven-Up.
Enjoy!

title: crab spread
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Spread in serving dish.
Top with cocktail sauce and then shredded crab meat.

title: miriam's tamale pie
directions: Bring water to a hot boil and add the 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Slowly add the cornmeal and cook over low heat for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Using a spoon or spatula, line an 8-cup casserole which has been lightly greased with 2/3 of the hot cornmeal mush, bringing it up the side as far as it will reach. If mush is too thick to spread, add a little boiling water.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Generously butter 10-inch pie or quiche dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs bottom and top; shake out excess.
Set aside.
Combine potatoes, onion, 3/4 cup Swiss cheese, butter, 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning, salt and pepper in a medium mixing bowl.
Stir gently; mix.
Spoon into pie plate and press firmly.
Bake in 450° preheated oven for 25 minutes.
Heat oil in large skillet. Add zucchini, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes; stir 5 minutes.
Spoon zucchini mixture in baked crust with slotted spoon.
Spread evenly in crust. Sprinkle with remaining 1 3/4 Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese. Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted; cut into wedges.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Coat mushrooms with remaining ingredients.
Place in baking pan; cover bottom with foil.
Place on grill.
Stir occasionally until done.

title: chili con queso
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease loaf pan with shortening.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center of bread comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove from pan. Let cool completely before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: school lunch
directions: Boil egg the night before.
Shell and cut in half.
Take yolk and mix with mayonnaise, salt and pepper; put back into egg white. Put into small bowl with lid.

title: basic whole wheat bread
directions: Pour water into a large mixing bowl and sprinkle with yeast. Allow yeast to dissolve (about 5 minutes).
Add honey, salt, dry milk, oil and 2 cups flour.
Stir well.
Continue to stir, adding a little flour at a time, until the dough becomes stiff and pulls away from sides of the bowl.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead 5 to 7 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic.
Shape dough and place in oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Allow loaf to rise in warm place until doubled.
Preheat oven to 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: parmesan spread
directions: Stir together and use.

title: candy kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Beat shortening and peanut butter in large bowl until well blended.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add milk, egg & vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat mixture gradually into peanut butter mixture. Roll mixture into 1 inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Immediately press a kiss into center of each cookie.
Cool on cookie sheet a few minutes before removing.

title: quick and easy white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cool 5 cups warm water with honey and oil.
Add the two mixtures to the flour and salt; mix and knead well.
Let rise.
Knead down and form into loaves.
Let rise in pans, then bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: viola's carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Blend well.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350°
for 30 minutes or until done (toothpick placed in center should come out dry).

title: pecan log
directions: Mix cream, sugar and vanilla together.
Your mix will be very dry.
Shape into 5 logs.
Wrap in foil and chill 2-3 hours. Combine caramel and water in top of double boiler.
Stir until melted. Dip logs into caramel and roll in pecans.
Chill 1 hour. Cut into slices and serve.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Cook meat until pink is gone; drain off grease.
Mix other ingredients with meat.
Serve warm.

title: coffee-toffee bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together butter or margarine and brown sugar, creaming well.
Blend in almond extract and instant coffee.
Add the dry ingredients gradually; blend thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate morsels and chopped almonds.
Press into a well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If desired, frost while still warm.

title: polish goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain off fat.
In a large baking dish, combine all ingredients, except the bread crumbs. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Grate cheese. Add other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and then egg whites.
Batter will be real stiff.* Bake in 275° to 300° oven in tube pan for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Let cool 20 to 25 minutes in pan.

title: blink of eye pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: tasty meat pie
directions: Roll 3/4 of the dough to fit 2-quart casserole.
Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Add catsup, Tabasco sauce and water to the meat.
Pour meat mixture onto dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with remaining dough.
Seal and cut vents.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Boil for 1 minute the sugar, cream of tartar and water.
Beat egg white.
Add cooked mixture and marshmallows.
Beat until it forms peaks.
Add vanilla.
Frosts 1 (9 x 13-inch) cake or 30 cupcakes.

title: refrigerate slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, cover with water and salt.
Let sit at least 1 hour.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil for 1 minute.
Let cool. Drain water from cabbage (squeeze out if necessary).
Pour other ingredients over cabbage and store in tightly sealed container.
(I use more vinegar for my taste.
The recipe is a little too sweet, so adjust to your taste.)

title: fresh apple loaf
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift flour, measure and sift with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with apples and nuts.
Stir to stiff batter.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: e z rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Follow directions on box for making pudding.
Add cinnamon and raisins.
Add rice a little at a time.
Mix well.
Chill 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Grate cheese.
Knead all together and make in rolls.
Roll in chili powder, chill and slice.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into an ungreased baking dish. Bake at 350° until browning on top, approximately 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with your favorite small cracker.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Baste meat frequently the last hour of cooking.

title: weight watchers baby ruth candy
directions: Mix and wrap in Handi-Wrap.
Chill.
Makes 1 serving.
Per serving:
3 pro., 1 br, 1 m, 3 f, 10 opt cal.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place pretzels in large shallow baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over pretzels.
Stir well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute or until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Spread between layers, and on side and top of your favorite cake.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In a small bowl, mash avocados to a smooth pulp.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until combined.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 3 cups, about 25 calories per tablespoon.

title: microwave crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients, except butter.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 12 to 14 minutes on High, or until apples are tender.

title: ann's fried rice(wok)
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Set aside.
Prepare all other ingredients in separate containers and set aside.
Heat wok to 300°.
Add peanut oil and heat 1 minute.
Add meat and stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add onions, celery and garlic; stir-fry 1 1/2 minutes.
Add peas and stir-fry 1 minute.
Add hot rice and stir until well mixed.
Make a hole or well in the center of rice, with bottom of wok showing, and add beaten eggs.
Let stand 1 minute, then slowly stir eggs in well until they are scrambled egg consistency.
Mix egg into rice mixture.
Make another well in center of rice and add soy sauce.
Let come to a boil and mix well with rice mixture.
Serve with soy sauce to season to taste.

title: fudge walnut brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 inch pie plate.
Beat eggs in large bowl and stir in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt and stir into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into prepared pie plate. Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Garnish with whipped cream or serve with ice cream, if desired.
Serves 6-8.

title: smoked fish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill one hour before serving.
Great with Triscuits or Wheat Thins.

title: lemon pie
directions: Pour lemonade in bowl.
Pour in Eagle Brand milk and whip. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in 1 graham cracker crust pie shell.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Place all ingredients directly from package to a large mixing bowl.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: cabbage soup(diabetic-low cholesterol-weight loss)
directions: Boil fryer tender the day before; place in refrigerator and skim fat off the broth.
Bring to boil; remove chicken and cool. Add vegetables to the boiling broth and cook until just tender. Add the tomatoes and chicken.
Again bring to a simmer for a few minutes, adding bouillon cubes and pepper to taste.
She says the "pepper makes the soup."

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt and combine with first mixture. Form into walnut-size balls and roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place on ungreased baking sheet approximately 2-inches apart and bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wild rice chicken
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Melt butter in saucepan and saute onion until light golden.
Add flour, salt and pepper; blend.
Gradually add milk, cream and chicken broth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Add rice, chicken, pimiento and parsley; mix well. Turn into an oiled 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until piping hot.
(Freezes well.)

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Remove from heat and add chicken, chili sauce, sour cream and salt.
In a flat, shallow bowl, combine cream and chicken stock.

title: stir-fried broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli florets off the tops of the stalks.
Cut stalks into 1/2-inch pieces.
Wash and drain.
Heat large skillet.
Add oil.
When oil is hot, add garlic and cook for a few minutes (do not burn).
Add broccoli and toss with wooden spoon until all pieces are coated with oil and the broccoli turns bright green. Add chicken broth and cover pan.
Cook vegetables until crisp but tender (do not overcook).

title: neapolitan beef casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Brown the beef.
Add pepper, mushrooms, tomatoes and spinach.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add uncooked noodles and sauce.
Pour over all into the casserole dish; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Before serving, garnish with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
May be prepared ahead of time and frozen.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crunchy fruit salad chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours or longer.
Before serving, add nuts and mix.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add beaten yolks, then flour and pecans. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased baking pan. Bake at 300° for 25 or 30 minutes. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown onion and beef in skillet, then add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste along with 1 can refried beans.
Mix butter, flour, enchilada sauce, salt, pepper and cumin powder.
Dip tortillas in sauce.
Layer in pan 1 layer sauce and 1 layer filling with tortillas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Can also fill tortillas and roll, then cover with sauce and cheese.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (drain).
Melt oleo in pan and saute onion and celery until it looks clear.
Add soup, milk and cheese. Cook on low heat for a smooth sauce.
Mix well with 3 cups of cooked rice.
Spread in oblong dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hungary mans dip
directions: On low heat of crock pot, melt Velveeta cheese, add hamburger, salsa and Cheddar cheese. When cheese is completely melted, serve with corn chips, or your favorite chip.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup of soup with other ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Mix rest of soup with 1/3 cup of water. Pour over patties and bake 10 minutes more.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done.
When cool, punch holes in cake.
Pour 1 can Eagle Brand on top.
Put Cool Whip, coconut, grated cheese and cherries on top. Refrigerate.

title: quick and easy veggie soup
directions: Place fresh vegetables in Dutch oven with vegetable oil and cook until they start to get light brown.
Put ground beef in and brown.
Immediately add all other ingredients and simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Better if slow simmered for longer.
Makes about 4 quarts of soup.
Yummy!!
Serve with corn bread.

title: pea salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar until dissolved.
Add salt and oil; pour over ingredients.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: *One stick for the bottom of casserole dish at the beginning of recipe and 1 1/2 sticks, melted for topping.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain everything good.
Stir dry Jell-O into Cool Whip and add other things.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, in hot oil, cook roast until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup and 1 cup of the water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender, turning occasionally.
Add vegetables. Cover; cook 40 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 medium muffin cups (2 3/4-inches in diameter).
Mix thoroughly the shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternately with milk.

title: submarine buns
directions: Mix yeast, 1 cup of warm water and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; let rise until doubled.
Knead; cut out with Spam can 1/2-inch thick.
Stretch; let rise again. Brush with melted butter and bake.
Cool upside down.

title: hamburger tomato soup casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook noodles. Drain.
Put in casserole with tomato soup.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruited ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, combine the milk, yogurt and lime juice. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except strawberries.
Cook until thick; let cool.
Put berries into baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over them; let chill.
You can use raspberries, fresh peaches or blackberries.
Just by the jello flavor to match your fruit.

title: lemony asparagus
directions: Place cooked asparagus in shallow greased casserole in single layer.
Melt butter until golden brown.
Blend in mayonnaise, seasonings and lemon juice; pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with crumbs, then cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes, or until browned.
Can be prepared in advance and reheated.

title: soda cracker bars
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix soup, mayo, onions and cheese and layer on top of veggies.
Bake at 325° until bubbly, about 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake 5 to 10 more minutes (until onion rings brown slightly).

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add baking soda, coconut and chips.
Mix well.
Work in dry ingredients; alternating flour and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar.
Using hands, mix in flour.
If dough is crumbly, mix in 1 to 2 tablespoons butter, softened.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut into small squares.
Place about 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until set but not brown, 20 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet. Cool completely. Store in tightly covered container up to 4 days.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: glazed country-style pork ribs
directions: Arrange ribs in 3-quart (13 x 9-inch) glass baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave for 15 minutes on Roast.
Drain off fat. Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; mix well and pour over ribs.
Re-cover and continue cooking for 35 or 40 minutes on Roast or until fork-tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: classic baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon to crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon. In 3-quart casserole, combine bacon, pork and beans, onion, ketchup, molasses, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every 20 minutes.
About 12 servings.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Grease oblong baking dish.
Layer, starting with zucchini, salt and pepper, onions and tomatoes.
Repeat layers; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with croutons and more cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted and brown.

title: shoney's fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake deep dish pie shell.
Cool.
Mix sugar, Jell-O, cornstarch and boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool completely.
Fill cooled crust with 1 quart fresh strawberries. Spoon cooled mixture over berries.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the noodles and cheeses and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook 9 noodles according to package directions. Layer 3 noodles, sauce and cheese; 3 noodles, sauce and cheese; 3 noodles, sauce and Mozzarella.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: san francisco stir-fry(beef)
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add beef; cook and stir until no longer pink.
In a small bowl, combine jelly, cornstarch and mustard.
Blend well.
Add jelly mixture and frozen vegetables to meat.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: virginia's champagne punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in lemon juice.
Add fruit and pour over block of ice in a punch bowl.
Dust before serving.
Add champagne and stir.
More champagne may be added as needed.

title: fast-n-fun doughnuts
directions: Separate biscuit dough from a can of biscuits.
Cut a hole in the center of each biscuit.
Fry in hot oil (about 350°) until golden on both sides, drain.
Shake in a bag with cinnamon and sugar or powdered sugar.
Can also be iced.
Serve immediately.

title: "sour cream pound cake"
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks until well blended.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Beat flour mixture into margarine mixture, one cup at a time, until well blended. Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Prep time:
15 minutes.
Cooking Time:
1 1/2 hours.

title: extra light extra delicious red stuff
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add diet coke.
Let set in refrigerator until partially set.
Stir in pineapple, pie filling and nuts.
Let chill until firm.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake, a few at a time, in bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.

title: savory tomato soup
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend in flour.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon; cook and stir until slightly thick.
Reduce heat and cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with bacon.

title: old fashioned fried quail
directions: Split cleaned quail lengthwise; wash then dry.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; sprinkle over quail.
Roll pieces of meat to coat.
In a heavy skillet or an electric frypan, melt margarine and brown meat.
Add water; simmer for 20 minutes.
Turn meat during cooking time; do not allow to boil dry.
If liquid level falls below 1/2 cup, add more water.
Add mushrooms, parsley, bouillon and cream; sprinkle with paprika.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes, or until tender.
Turn meat during cooking time once or twice.
Do not allow sauce to cook away.
If necessary, add additional cream and water (in equal portions).

title: pineapple cheesecake(makes 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; blend well.
Press firmly onto bottom and side of a 9-inch spring-form pan or a quiche or tart pan with a removable bottom.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Stir in pineapple. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 minutes or until center is set.
While cheesecake is baking, mix sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove cheesecake from oven.
Spread sour cream mixture on top.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill well before serving.

title: italian delight
directions: The day before, cook macaroni as label directs; drain.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium size bowl. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: cold seafood mousse
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Let stand to blend flavors. Combine soup and cream cheese in top of double boiler.
Heat over boiling water, stirring until cheese is melted.
Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Add to soup mixture.
Stir until dissolved. Remove from heat; cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, blend in mayonnaise and fish mixture.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart mold. Chill until set.
Serve with mayonnaise.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Rinse.
Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: onion flower
directions: Cut onion from top into 8 wedges with onion opening, but remaining together.
Place bouillon cube and butter into center of onion.
Place in microwavable bowl.
Microwave for 2 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture starting and ending with flour. Preheat oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal pone (supper cake)
directions: Mix all together; bake in moderate oven.

title: mammaw's persimmon pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: barbecued onions
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 4 to 5 minutes; stirring occasionally.
Stir in onion, cover and simmer 3 minutes. Cover and chill.
Serve with vegetables and barbecued meats.

title: strawberry rhubarb clouds
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In a medium bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually sprinkle in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition and until sugar dissolves and whites stand in stiff glossy peaks.

title: barbecued beef(for a crowd)
directions: Chop peppers, onions and celery; cook with hamburg.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
Serves 50.

title: pirogies
directions: Dough:
Mix 2 cups of flour, salt and sour cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop up the onion and pepper. Cook with hamburger meat slowly in small amount of oleo until meat is done. Drain.
Mix pork and beans, sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Add meat to beans mixture.
Put into pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: domino brownies
directions: Cook brownies as prepared on package.
After brownies have cooled, put frosting on.
Cut in 6 lengthwise strips about 1 1/2 inches wide.
Cut in 4 crosswise strips 3 inches wide.
Remove brownies from pan.
Run knife through frosting across center to divide in half.
Use chocolate chips to decorate like dominos.

title: oriental salad
directions: Cut up green onions.
In large bowl, mix cabbage and green onions.
Place almonds, sunflower seeds and noodles from both packages of soup on a cookie sheet.
Put in oven at 350° until lightly browned.
Put in plastic bag or bowl.
Mix oil, sugar and seasoning packet from both packages of soup.
Add to cabbage and onions and stir.
Just before ready to eat, add the almonds, seeds and noodles; stir.
These are double batch ingredients.

title: honey cream carrots
directions: Cut carrots in 2-inch strips.
Cook them in salt water and drain.
Melt butter and add ginger.
Add carrots, honey and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently until carrots are heated through.
Then fold in almonds.

title: steak - n - potato
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Poke steak all over with a fork on both sides.
Combine 1 cup of flour, seasoned salt, pepper and salt.
Dip steak into flour mixture and put in hot oil.
Fry until brown on each side.
Pour a thin layer of gravy into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add meat.
Slice potatoes into wedges and put over meat.
Pour rest of gravy onto potatoes.
If needed, add some water so potatoes are almost covered with gravy.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: moon cake
directions: Boil water and oleo and add flour; stir.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Put on greased pan and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool.

title: sausage potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onions until soft.
Cut sausage into bite-size pieces.
Add to potatoes.
Add water to make consistency of soup desired.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large ovenproof Dutch oven. Cover with water to 2 inches above beans and bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes, remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain beans and return to pan.
Add 8 cups water and onions; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Drain bean mixture and return to pan.
Add barbecue sauce and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 16 servings.

title: banana mandarin cream cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth. Stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice and vanilla. Slice 2 bananas; dip in lemon juice and drain. Line crust with bananas and about 2/3 of the orange segments. Pour filling over fruit. Chill 3 hours or until set. Before serving, slice remaining banana; dip in lemon juice and drain. Garnish top with banana slices and remaining orange segments. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients well and pour into casserole dish. Prepare topping as listed below:

title: miss nancy's chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to butter mixture with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Cook in 3 pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry cream tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll one of the pie crusts out, forming an 11 x 14-inch rectangle.
Cut 12 circles out of crust.
Place circles into mini muffin pan to form miniature pie shells.
Repeat using second pie crust.
Prick tart shells.
Bake shells 10 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Pour liquid mixture over apples and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Test for doneness with knife blade.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into crusts.
Chill until firm.

title: cornbread pie
directions: In a 8 by 8 inch pan mix beans & chicken.
Pour BBQ sauce over all.
Mix cornbread according to package directions, pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 12-18 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat all but cake mix, margarine and nuts. Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top. Pour melted margarine over cake mix and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, no longer. Top with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini squash soup
directions: Wash,
peel and cook squash and onion in water.
Drain; put in blender or mash with masher.
Add milk, butter, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 to 8 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: In a large saucepan combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes until berries pop.
Cool.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate apricot fondant
directions: In a small bowl, soak apricots in brandy for 1 hour.
Line an 11 x 4-inch loaf pan with plastic wrap.
Melt chocolate with Espresso coffee in top of a double boiler over low heat, stirring well.
Add butter, a bit at a time, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, beat egg yolks until pale yellow and fluffy.
Fold in apricots and brandy.
Slowly pour chocolate mixture into egg and apricot mixture; gently fold to blend.
Cool for 30 minutes.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until firm, but not stiff.
Fold gently into chocolate mixture.
Pour into plastic-lined loaf pan and freeze for 6 hours.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Top with whipped cream and apricots.

title: squash casserole supreme
directions: Combine and stir.
Put 1/2 of stuffing in mixture and stir. Pour in oblong buttered casserole dish.
Pour rest of Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese and add powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk, beat until thick. Spread over cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and cover with shaved or grated chocolate.

title: megan's taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown onion and ground beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain well.
Add sugar; cook for 1 minute.
Add chili powder; cook another minute.
Add barbecue sauce; mix.
Add only enough ketchup to color meat (should be a little dry).
Cook for 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Chop the well drained head of lettuce; add cheese.
Add only enough dressing to lightly cover.
Add meat to lettuce; mix.
Crumble chips on top and serve.
Do not mix ahead, or lettuce and chips will become soggy.

title: coffee egg nog punch
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine egg nog, brown sugar, coffee and cinnamon; beat on low speed until sugar and coffee are dissolved. Stir in coffee, liqueur and bourbon (if desired); chill.
In small mixer bowl, beat cream with confectioners sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Pour egg nog into punch bowl; top with whipped cream and cinnamon.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly and cut into small squares for appetizers or larger ones for a vegetable side dish.

title: spritz
directions: Soften butter.
Grate almonds in processor until powder fine. Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add egg and extract and beat until blended.
On low speed, blend in flour, salt and almonds. Mix until incorporated.
Fill cookie press and press in desired shapes onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Roll fish in melted butter and then in cracker crumbs.
Put into pan.
Add more butter.
Bake at 400° until nice and brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Optional:
Add small pieces of fruit (example: peach or apple, and cook with fruit.
Or serve with heated Comstock cherry or blueberry pie filling on the side.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in slices, cook in salted water and drain thoroughly.
Mash to a pulp.
Add butter and stir.
Add eggs, milk, crumbs and onion. Pour into grated 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Layer remaining ingredients in dish as listed over cocktail sauce (it works well in clear dish, it is very colorful).
Serve on crackers.

title: sis' potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash and add other ingredients. Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until center is set and crust browned.

title: caribbean pork
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss well to coat.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add pork mixture and saute for 4 minutes or until done.
Serve with rice and vegetables or in vegetable stir-fry and with warm rolls.
Serves 4.

title: tuna cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Stir in cornmeal and onion flakes.
Combine buttermilk, egg and oil.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients; stir well but do not beat.
Fold in olives and tuna.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: garden supper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix bread cubes, cheese and 2 tablespoons butter; spread half the mixture in greased 1-quart casserole and top with peas.
Cook and stir onion in 3 tablespoons butter until onion is tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in meat; pour over peas.
Arrange tomato slices on top and sprinkle with remaining bread mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crawfish boil leftovers casserole
directions: Peel and chop crawfish tails, discarding fat.
Mix potatoes as you would for mashed or creamed potatoes, using buttermilk or cream and Velveeta.
Season as you would, using salt and pepper or any Creole seasoning.
Mix in crawfish pieces.
Spread into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two cake pans.
Sprinkle grated cheese
on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese is melted. You may add green onions, sour cream of other ingredients to spice up the casserole to your taste.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: daddy's custard
directions: First
take
coconut
milk,
heat 2 1/2 cups whole milk. Add 2
cups
flaked
or
shredded coconut.
Simmer 10 minutes. Pour into
blender
container and whirl at highest speed until coconut is finely ground.
Strain through strainer.
Beat eggs until whites
are no longer stringy (eggs should not be foamy). Add sugar
and
coconut
milk.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Blend evaporated
milk,
cardamon, mace, cloves and flavoring. Pour into
baking
dish,
place dish into pot half-filled with boiling water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes
out clean.
Cool, cover and chill, decorate with coconut.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: In saucepan, combine potatoes, onions, bouillon and water. Boil for 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Put into blender and blend on high until smooth.
Pour into bowls and top with bacon bits.
Makes 4 cups.

title: oatmeal crunch bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well; press in greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 22 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 48.

title: viki vogt's italian beef
directions: Marinate roast in oily Italian dressing after studding the roast with garlic cloves or powder.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Beat cream cheese on medium speed until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Line muffin tins with cupcake liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over wafers, filling liners full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Put chilled cherry (or your preference) pie filling on top before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef, crumble and drain well.
In a large bowl mix together taco sauce, chicken and rice soup, cream of chicken soup, beans and tomatoes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Combine next 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon in prepared dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick skillet casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain grease. Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Add to ground beef and onion. Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, then add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add bananas and nuts, then fold in dry ingredients, sifted.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: nut or poppy seed rolls
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese together, then add flour.
Mix good.
Chill overnight.
Next day, roll out; spread nut mixture or whatever filling you want.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top gets nice and brown.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in a baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: low-fat devil's food surprise
directions: Prepare as directed on box.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple and oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream or yogurt with sugar and stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin and water; mix well.
Mix in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat well; add raisins and nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves or 3 (1 pound) coffee cans, floured and greased.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly grease a casserole dish and line with bread slices. Cover bread with grated cheese then cover with sausage.
Mix together eggs with dash of garlic and mushrooms.
Pour egg mixture over sausage and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is set.
(Don't over bake or get too brown.)

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with 2/3 cup sugar; let stand 1 hour. Heat oven to 400°.
Mix baking mix, 3 tablespoons sugar, margarine and milk until soft dough forms.
Drop dough in 6 mounds onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 or 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Split shortcake; fill and top with strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies(low-fat)
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter, peanut butter and sugars. Add egg white; beat until blended. Beat in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Shape into an 8-inch roll.
Wrap in plastic.
Freeze for 2 hours or until firm.
Unwrap and cut into slices about 1/4-inch thick. Place 2-inches apart on baking sheet, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies, 8 to 10 minutes of crisp cookies.
Cool 1 to 2 minutes before removing to wire racks.
Cool completely. Makes 2 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and mash baked sweet potatoes; add margarine.
Beat in eggs, then add milk, sugar and flavoring.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Put mixture into 2 baked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Graham cracker shells work fine for these pies, but do not prebake them.

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Put 2/3 of batter in a Bundt pan.
Mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Add rest of batter. Bake at 350° until done, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spicy sausage and red gravy
directions: *If using turkey sausage, 1 tablespoon of canola oil will be needed to brown the sausage.

title: beef bourbonnaise
directions: Heat bacon drippings.
Add onions and mushrooms; cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
Remove onions and mushrooms; reserve drippings.
Add steak and cook, turning occasionally, until browned on all sides.
Sprinkle flour, salt, marjoram or rosemary, pepper and thyme over meat; stir so that ingredients are well blended.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough mayonnaise for desired consistency.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Red and white cabbage may be added.

title: grandmother pearson's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then all other ingredients.
Drop cookies with a tablespoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Great to eat hot from the oven.
Store in airtight container.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Combine blueberries, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Place into an 8-inch square pan.
Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar; add milk. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Spread batter over blueberries.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pork tenderloin towers
directions: Slice pork tenderloin and flatten slices to 1/2-inch thick. Place in baking pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place thick slice of onion, thick slice of tomato and two half slices of bacon on each piece of pork tenderloin.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven, uncovered.
(If you wish bacon crisp, place pan under broiler for a few minutes.)

title: almond milk
directions: Blend almonds with small amount of water first, then add remaining water and ingredients.
Whiz until smooth; strain, chill and serve.

title: white butter icing
directions: In a bowl or food processor, beat butter, milk and half the powdered sugar until smooth.

Stir in remaining sugar and the vanilla and beat until creamy (about 3 minutes with a spoon or hand held electric beater or about 30 seconds in food processor). If too stiff, add a few additional drops of milk.

title: chinese crunch salad
directions: Slice cabbage very thin and toss with onions.
Melt butter. Crush Ramen noodles.
Add noodles, sesame seed and almonds to melted butter.
Brown, then cool.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Toss all ingredients together.

title: creole noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Cook and stir onion and green pepper in margarine in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Stir in yogurt, chili sauce and mustard.
Heat, stirring constantly, just until hot.
Add noodles and toss until coated with yogurt mixture.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except popcorn and baking soda). Dissolve over low heat.
Boil 5 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Put in oven at 250° for 30 minutes.
Stif often.
Pour onto cookie sheets and let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix juice of 1 lemon with enough sugar to make sweet.
Mix lemon juice with apple slices.
Coat well.
Mix brown sugar, both flours, oatmeal and margarine.
Use hands to mix ingredients. Grease Pyrex baking dish.
Spread apples in dish. Put oatmeal mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top should be browned.

title: crunchy ice cream dessert
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts in bowl.
Melt butter and brown sugar.
Pour over Rice Krispies mixture.
Spread 1/2 mixture in cake pan or Tupperware container.
Spread softened ice cream over mixture.
Cover with remaining 1/2 of mixture.
Freeze. Serve with thawed or fresh strawberries or raspberries or just plain.

title: pickled string beans
directions: Steam the beans 5 minutes or less.
Strain the juice off.
In a different pot, mix the pickling spices into the vinegar and liquid sweetener.
Bring to a boil.
Strain.
Pour over beans and let stand overnight.

title: leslie's pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Combine with dry ingredients. Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Pour in bread pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: In glass dish, combine all ingredients, except pork chops. Then add pork chops.
Cover and marinate 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Place chops on grill 5 to 7-inches above coals. Cook at low temperature 20 to 25 minutes or until done, turning chops occasionally and brushing frequently with marinade.

title: norwegian kringla
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in bowl.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and almond flavoring.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Chill, covered, for several hours to overnight.
Remove 1/4 of the dough at a time from refrigerator.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into 7-inch rope.
Shape as for pretzels on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Store between layers of paper towels in airtight container.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Cook angel food cake according to box.
Dissolve jello in 3 cups of boiling water.
Add strawberries and refrigerate until set, 1 hour.
Fold in half the Cool Whip.
Shread cake in small pieces. Sprinkle half the cake on bottom.
Cover with half the jello; repeat.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: crock-pot potatoes and ham
directions: Double if serving more than 6 people.

title: saucy ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and stir until melted.
Toss potatoes in cheese sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole, reserving 1 cup sliced potatoes.
Arrange ham and remaining potatoes on top of casserole. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tea punch
directions: Make tea with tea bags and boiling water.
While tea is hot, pour
over	the
sugar.
Mix
well, then add juices.
Mix well. Fill
container
to the top with water enough to make 1 gallon.

title: chocolate shakes
directions: Put 1/2 cup milk in blender; add 1 tablespoon chocolate malt. Blend.
Fill blender 3/4 full of ice cream.
Cover with milk. Blend until smooth.

title: favorite chicken and stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; place over stuffing.
Top with cheese.
Drizzle with butter. Combine soup and water; spoon over stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until chicken juices run clear.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: debby's shrimp dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, chili sauce, lemon juice and horseradish.
Fold in shrimp.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt in a large bowl.
Put egg in one-cup measuring cup and beat.
Add vinegar and finish filling cup with milk.
Add to flour; mix.
Roll to desired thickness. Yields 2 to 3 pie crusts.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Rinse, dry and count water chestnuts.
Mix with brown sugar. Cut bacon into strips (same number as chestnuts).
Wrap bacon around each chestnut, fastening with toothpicks.
This can be refrigerated for several hours before baking.
Bake at 450° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in large pot of salted water until tender, stirring occasionally. Drain. Add margarine and cheese to hot macaroni in the pot, reserving 1 cup cheese for topping. Add milk and cook on low heat until cheese is melted. Stir as needed. Break eggs into a bowl and beat until blended. Add to hot ingredients and stir until well blended. Mixture should be very soft. Add milk, if needed. Add small amount of salt and pepper. Pour into 4-quart Pyrex dish and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: danish puff
directions: Cut 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup butter together as for pie crust. Stir in 3 tablespoons water with a fork to form a soft dough. Divide dough in half and form into 2 oblongs about 4 inches wide and as long as a cookie sheet.
Use fingers to pat dough into shape.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in 1 cup boiling water.
Remove from heat and immediately add almond flavoring and 1 cup flour all at once.
Stir until dough leaves sides of kettle.
Put in small mixing bowl and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread on the 2 oblongs and bake about 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
While warm, frost puff with Toasted Coconut Icing.

title: rainbow molded salad(serves about 25 people)
directions: Grease a large Bundt cake pan with Crisco (not oil).
Dissolve the strawberry Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water and after cooling, place into greased pan.
Allow to set before adding next layer of Jell-O.
Dissolve orange Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/4 cup of juice from fruit cocktail and allow to cool.
Add fruit from can and add to strawberry Jell-O in mold after it has set.
Add orange Jell-O layer.
Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and add to orange mixture after it has set.

title: alma's corn fritters
directions: Mix Bisquick with enough milk to make a thick batter.
Add corn and onion flakes.
Have one inch of canola cooking oil (Heart Healthy) in deep skillet and drop by rounded teaspoonful in hot oil.
Drain and eat with applesauce or syrup.
Any fresh vegetables can be used.
Asparagus is great!

title: mel's apple butter
directions: Combine apples and water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 25 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Mash apples and stir in all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put mixture in pint jars; 1/4 inch from top.
Seal and put in boiling bath water for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad(great served at thanksgiving and christmas.)
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water until berries are all open. Add gelatin and marshmallows while hot.
Stir in other ingredients when cool.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: tropical sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Mix together corn flakes, melted butter and brown sugar.
Put half of mashed sweet potato in 8-inch square buttered baking dish.
Put one banana on top. Put rest of mashed sweet potatoes, then put second banana on top. Top with the corn flakes, brown sugar and butter mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: quick bread pudding
directions: Spread brown sugar in a 2-quart dish.
Place 3 to 4 slices of buttered and cubed bread on top of the sugar.
Pour egg and milk over all.

title: laurie's cream cheese brownies
directions: In a small bowl, beat together until smooth the cream cheese, 1/3 cup of the sugar and 1 egg.
In a medium pan, melt together over low heat, stirring constantly, the cocoa, butter and water. Add the following ingredients in pan:
the flour, 2 cups of sugar, 2 eggs, baking soda and salt.
When well mixed, stir in the sour cream.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Combine thawed potatoes with melted margarine, onion, sour cream, soup, salt and pepper.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix everything together; bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in a sheet pan.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Whip the cream until it peaks; add the sugar, then the rest and stir.
Chill and it's ready to eat.

title: grilled veggies
directions: Cut all of the vegetables in half lengthwise; core the peppers.
Combine butter, herbs and garlic salt.
Coat vegetables well with this mixture.
Place vegetables, cut side down, on grill.
Potatoes should be placed near the center.
Cook 10 minutes.
Turn vegetables over, sprinkle with cheese; cook 10 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stir-fry vegetables(makes 4 servings)
directions: In skillet or wok, over medium-high heat, stir-fry broccoli, peppers and scallions in hot oil for 8 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in water chestnuts, steak sauce, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Cook and stir just until heated through.

title: pita pizzas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl. Toss gently. Place pita rounds on baking sheets coated with cooking spray. Spread 1/4 cup zucchini mixture on each pita round; sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cut each round into 8 wedges.
Serve hot.
Contains 13 calories per wedge.
Makes 64 wedges.

title: spicy tomato soup(quick)
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet. Add remaining ingredients. Stir and heat thoroughly. Garnish with avocado or cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon poppy seed crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, sugar and milk in mixing bowl.
Stir in muffin mix until well blended.
Drop round teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Makes approximately 20 (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: laura's lane cake
directions: Cream the butter and add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with milk; begin and end with flour. Beat egg whites
and fold into batter. Add vanilla.
Pour batter into 3 layer cake pans (greased and dusted with a little flour). Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Place manicotti shells in baking pan and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
In a small bowl, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix well, then stuff in shells.
Then combine herb sauce, water, Burgundy and Parmesan in large bowl.
Cover shells in baking pan after filled and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian tomatoes
directions: Rinse and cut tomatoes in bite-size pieces.
Add onions and parsley.
Set aside.

title: coconut-pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.
Store in refrigerator.
(The recipe called for 1 1/2 cups sugar, but I use 3/4 cup of sugar.)

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour small amount over egg yolks, stirring vigorously.
Return to pan and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: bean salad
directions: Boil 5 minutes and pour over vegetables, mixing well and refrigerate.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown ground beef with sausage.
Drain.
Add to meat mixture the Worcestershire sauce, oregano and garlic powder.
Stir in cheese and combine until cheese melts.
Spread on bread.
Put on cookie sheets and heat in oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa
directions: Drain juice from tomatoes into blender.
Add garlic, red pepper, cilantro, cumin and salt.
Blend on high until well blended.
Add tomatoes and green onions.
Blend gently for 1 to 2 seconds or stir with spoon for chunky salsa.
Add more or less of any of the spices to fit your taste.

title: shrimp pate
directions: Place all the ingredients in the blender and blend until smooth.
Transfer the mixture to an oiled bowl.
Chill the pate for 4 hours before serving.
Unmold onto a serving plate and decorate with greens and shrimp with shell on.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sugar, vanilla, chopped nuts, eggs and sour cream together.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle on mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour rest of batter over the cinnamon mix.
Bake at 325° until cake is done, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling.

title: brisket
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Make into small balls and press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 8 layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order in shallow dish.
Bean dip, avacado's, sprinkle with lemon juice and garlic salt.
Mix 3 T. sour cream, mayo, and taco seasoning together and layer on mixture.
