Layer tomatoes, onions, olives and add cheese dip. Serve hot or cold.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together and press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter; add mushroom soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Mix in cooked rice and frozen broccoli.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: best gourmet meat loaf
directions: Mix all very well.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (shape as loaf or 2 small loaves).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash and bake potatoes until done. Scald cream by heating almost to a boil.
Meanwhile, saute onion in butter until translucent.
When potatoes are cooled, cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp into large bowl. With electric mixer, mash potatoes.
Add onions, mushrooms, cheese and half and half or cream. Mix until fluffy.
Pile whipped potato mixture back into potato shells.
Top with a little cheese and bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated and cheese is melted.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients and apples and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Brown hamburger until red is gone.
Drain and set aside.
Add a small amount of oil, potatoes and carrots to skillet and cook until lightly brown, but still firm, stirring often. Add onion, browned hamburger, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and saute on low heat until potatoes and carrots are tender and onion is limp. Add corn and beans.
Cook over low heat until all is hot and flavors blend, about 5 minutes. Serve with hot bread, rolls or cornbread.

title: hettie pruitt's easter ham
directions: Mix mustard and brown sugar to prepare a thin paste.
Rub paste over ham that has been scored.
Pour cola over ham.
Wrap in heavy foil and bake according to directions on ham package.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread slices. Reserve crusts.
Spread butter over 1 side of each bread slice.
Place bread slices, buttered side up, in bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Set aside.
Brown sausage in large skillet, stirring until it crumbles. Drain.
Spoon sausage over bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half an half and salt and pour over cheese. Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator. Let stand, covered for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden. Yield:
8 servings.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup; boil until it spins a thread. Add nuts, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until it turns brownish gold.
Remove from heat and add butter, salt and soda. Pour onto buttered board to cool.
As candy cools, work up from board with spatula.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 325° (uncovered).
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with 3/4 cup herbed Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Sprinkle over chicken and return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly. Drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Chill.
Shape in 6 to 8 croquettes, shaping around each cube of cheese.
Roll in egg and cracker crumbs.
Saute in about 1-inch of hot fat until well browned on all sides.
Good served on bun with lettuce.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems.
Chop stems finely and saute with onions, garlic, margarine until liquid evaporates.
In a bowl, combine cooked mixture with bread crumbs, cheese, oil, parsley, and oregano, salt and pepper.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture using last tablespoon oil to brush on top of stuffed mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onions, then set aside.
Brown ground meat; drain grease. Mix the sauteed onions into the browned ground meat; add mushrooms and 1/2 to 3/4 of the jar of Ragu and place in rectangular baking dish.
Spread a layer of sour cream over the ground meat mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese over sour cream layer.
Roll out the crescent rolls over the cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until rolls brown).

title: tuna-mushroom canapes
directions: To tuna, add soup, pimiento, green pepper and seasonings. Blend.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place on a baking sheet.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 5 minutes until cheese browns.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: norwegian apple cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add apple, stirring lightly to coat.
Combine egg and vanilla, add to apple mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Spoon mixture into a 9-inch pie plate, coated with cooking spray.
Arrange almonds as desired on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 6 servings (approximately 172 calories per serving, fat 3.3).

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix 24 hours ahead of time.
Scoop out center of round dark bread; cube scooped out bread for dip.
Fill cavity of bread with dip.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the apples, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Beat eggs. Gradually add the 2 cups sugar and oil.
Beat well together.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt together. Add egg mixture to flour, alternating with orange juice. Add vanilla. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour half of the batter into pan. Add half of the apples. Add rest of the batter and top with the rest of the apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and	milk
to
boil and add peanuts. Cook until a medium firm ball will form in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla,
butter,
powdered sugar and red food coloring.
Beat until
it thickens.
Drop into buttered muffin tins or pour onto buttered	wax
paper.
If
put
on
the
wax paper, it may be cut into circles with a biscuit cutter before it gets completely cold.

title: brown sugar candy
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook butter, brown sugar and milk over medium fire for 7 minutes.
Get your electric beater ready. Add the powdered sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into pan and cool for 1/2 hour before cutting.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender.
Drain. Set aside.
Saute carrots, onions, pepper in butter until done.
Mix together with zucchini in greased 9 x 13 dish.
In small bowl mix sour cream, soup and cheese, combine with zucchini mixture.
Stir in croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter meringues
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually and beat until mixture will hold firm peaks.
Fold in vanilla and peanut butter very gently until barely mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls (be sure to have some meringue and peanut butter in each) on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 1 minute.
Remove to rack and cool thoroughly.

title: super-duper chocolate cookies
directions: Mix and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Flatten with fork on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: cheese puff balls
directions: Add all but rice, mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and roll into balls.
Flatten slightly, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit and chicken
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour half of mixture over chicken pieces.
Bake 1 hour (or a little more) at 350°.
After first half hour, baste with remaining sauce.
The last 5 minutes, top with small can of pineapple chunks, small can of mandarin oranges and a dozen cherries.
Sufficient for 2 chickens.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Add water to tone down the vinegar. Cook about 30 minutes. Can be sealed in jars.

title: our christmas punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze in container. This will become flaky.
I use a fork to flake off in punch bowl. This amount calls for 3 quarts of ginger ale.
You may use orange, grapefruit or combinations of juices for the amounts called for.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in slow cooker.
Cook 6 hours on low heat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut cake into small squares.
Layer with all the ingredients except Cool Whip.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
You can also use bananas.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and place in brown grocery bag.
Mix together in a 4-cup measuring cup and cook on High in microwave for 3 minutes the next 3 ingredients.
Remove from oven and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour liquid mixture over popped corn in bag and shake or stir with long-handled wooden spoon.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High. Open bag, shake and close bag.
Microwave again 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Open bag, shake and close bag. Microwave 30 seconds on High.
Pour corn onto waxed paper-covered cookie sheet(s) to cool.
When cool, break apart and store in plastic bag or eat it!

title: crab ragoons
directions: Mix crabmeat, cream cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Brush wonton skins with egg.
Put teaspoonful crabmeat mixture in center of wonton skin.
To close, bring one corner to the center, two sides to the center and bring the other end up to the center. Seal with a touch of egg.
Deep fry until brown.
Drain.

title: pork chops on rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a covered baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Microwave cheese, soup and butter just to melt.
Stir in potatoes.
You can bake with chops, chicken or hot dogs on top. Takes about 1
hour at 450° or use crock-pot and cook slow all day.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: In a small saucepan, stir gelatine into 1/2 cup pineapple juice; stir over low heat until gelatine is dissolved. Pour into large bowl; stir in remaining juice. Chill until syrupy. Stir in marshmallows, sweetened condensed milk, pineapple, celery and shredded carrots. Pour into 2-quart mold. Chill until firm.

title: ranch style stew
directions: Brown beef lightly in butter.
Add hot water and cook 1 hour. Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper.
Stir in flour.
Add water to cover as needed.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Use large electric frypan or large frypan.
After 20 minutes, add dumplings.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut; mix all ingredients and allow to set overnight. May store refrigerated indefinitely.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat.
Add the onion and leek and saute, stirring often, until soft, about 8 minutes.
Stir in the pumpkin, chicken broth and spices.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Puree mixture in a processor.
Can be refrigerated for 2 days or frozen.
Return puree to saucepan; add the half and half and stir over moderate heat until heated through. Adjust seasoning as desired.
Garnish with chives.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg well; add sugar, flour, baking powder and salt to egg mixture.
Blend well; add apple, nuts and vanilla.

title: chewy cake dessert
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Mix until it looks like dough.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and box of sugar except 1/4 cup of sugar.
In a 13 x 9-inch rectangle pan, press dough in bottom, making the sides higher.
Pour 2nd mixture in the center.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar after baking.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time; fold in flour.
Add vanilla and nuts last.
Bake in greased baking pan at 350° until done.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well and divide in half.
Makes 2 rolls.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not bake any longer than time specified.

title: skinny eggs bennie
directions: Toast English muffin halves and place one-half on each of 4 plates.
Gently poach eggs until desired doneness.
While eggs are poaching, make cheese sauce.
In a small saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour to make a roux (thick paste) and cook, stirring, for 30 seconds.
Using a whisk, stir in milk and continue stirring until mixture thickens (about 3 minutes).
Stir in cheese, Worcestershire and mustard until cheese has melted. Place a slice of ham on each muffin half.
Top with poached egg. Spoon sauce evenly over eggs.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "low-fat" meatless lasagna
directions: Cook, drain and cool noodles.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the parsley, oregano, salt and pepper with the Ricotta cheese.
Cover the bottom of pan with sauce.
Then layer the noodles, cheese, mushrooms and sauce.
When all the ingredients have been used, cover the lasagna with the Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix by hand, cake mix, egg and margarine, and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in blender until smooth, the following:
powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for
40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: tamale dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese melts.
Serve warm with taco chips.
Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: ho ho bars
directions: Mix all together and put into greased and floured 14 1/2 x 10 1/2 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine 3 beans, onions and sweet pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: cornish hen with rice
directions: Salt and pepper the Cornish hens.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Instead of 2 1/2 cups of water, use 3 cups of water.
Pour Rice-A-Roni into baking dish.
Then put Cornish hens into mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring brown sugar, oleo and cream to a boil.
Add powdered sugar, nuts and vanilla.

title: potato torte
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water and add mashed potatoes.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Continue beating, add dry ingredients and milk.
Add chocolate mixture.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
To fresh tortillas, dip in hot fat and drain.
The tortillas should still be soft.
To make sauce, mix 1/2 of cheese with soup.
Add 2/3 soup can of milk.
Stir in green chili.
To make casserole, put spoonful of sauce in dish as it greasing it.
Then layer tortillas and cheese sauce.
Cover with remaining cheese sauce.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt in saucepan 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend in 2 tablespoons flour.
Slowly add 1 1/2 cups milk and asparagus liquid.
When sauce boils, reduce heat and add 1 cup grated cheese.
Cook until melted.
In saucepan, melt 1/4 butter.
Add cracker crumbs and brown them.
Add nuts.
In casserole dish, place drained asparagus.
Pour sauce over asparagus.
Sprinkle browned crumbs and nut mixture over the top.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl mix all dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes in the mix and add vinegar in one hole, vanilla in another hole and butter in 3rd hole. Add cold water and beat until mixed well.
Pour into ungreased sheet cake pan and bake for 25-30 minutes.

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: Brown meat with Italian seasoning in large skillet; drain. Combine spaghetti sauce and water in a small bowl.
Place 4 uncooked noodles in bottom of a lightly greased 5 quart slow cooker.
Layer with half each of beef mixture, spaghetti sauce mixture, and mushrooms.
Spread ricotta cheese over mushrooms. Sprinkle with 1 cup mozzarella cheese.
Layer with remaining noodles, meat, sauce, mushrooms and cheese.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour; reduce heat and cook on low for 5 hours.

title: mexican salad
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain. Add onion. Cook, stirring often until onion is tender. Stir in beans, dressing, water and chili powder. Simmer for 15 minutes. Combine lettuce and green onions in salad bowl. Add meat mixture and 1 1/2 cups cheese. Mix lightly. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: perfect prime rib
directions: Have meat at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Season meat.
Cook meat 1 hour.
Turn oven off.
Do not open door.
Leave off at least 40 minutes (can leave off hours).
Turn on and cook 40 minutes before you want to serve.
Use for 5 pounds or more.
For less than 5 pounds, cook only 30 minutes at end.
For 5 pounds rare, I do 30 minutes.
Trust me, it works.

title: fish parmesan
directions: Microwave fish, salt and butter covered with waxed paper on High for 2 minutes.
Mix cheese, onions and mayonnaise and spread over cooked fish and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with paprika when done.

title: spicy crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in egg, then coat with remaining ingredients.
Cook until chicken is done in a pan or dish sprayed with Pam.

title: french-style green beans and corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn; spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Spread over top of casserole.
Sprinkle generously with almonds.
Melt margarine. Sprinkle crushed crackers over casserole.
Pour margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly in the center.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, in large bowl.
Shape into loaf.
Put in slow cooker with the potatoes wrapped in foil beside the meat loaf.
Cover; cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: summer salad
directions: Chop fresh vegetables.
Mix vinegar, sugar and pepper until sugar is dissolved.
Pour liquid over vegetables; toss.
Cover and refrigerate.
Keeps good for 2 or more days.

title: lord supper bread
directions: Be reverent while you work.
Add enough flour to water to make dough.
Roll and fold it until air bubbles become small.
Roll thin.
Take a knife and score it, then put in 200° oven until it is done, not brown.
Break into small pieces.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: creamed dill carrots
directions: Slice or dice carrots.
Cook in salt water until tender. Drain.

title: pan chicken
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients like custard.
Place a layer of skinned and boned chicken in baking dish; alternate with cooked custard.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle on top of chicken.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; combine remaining ingredients (except garlic and parsley).
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over mushrooms and stir well.
Add garlic.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Stir and turn occasionally.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Drain and serve.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Place crust in spring-form (or angel food) cake pan and pour cheese batter over this.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Remove from oven and cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Add topping and return to oven and bake for 7 more minutes.

title: applesauce pancakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Blend in next 4 ingredients.
Beat egg yolks and add with margarine.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto hot greased griddle.
Makes about 10 pancakes.

title: hot anisette eggnog
directions: Combine water and rum in a percolator.
Put anise seed and powdered sugar in the percolator basket.
Perk.
In a small saucepan, combine custard mix and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove basket.
Add milk mixture to percolator.
Stir to blend.
Serve hot in mugs with nutmeg.
Can also be poured over ice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Slice off top of bread. Hollow out and save chunks of bread. Mix all ingredients, except bread. Fill bread shell, replace top and wrap in foil. Bake on cookie sheet for 1 hour.

title: prize winning recipe dutch ridge reunion cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Sift together in separate bowl flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Sift dry ingredients together then add to cream mixture; alternately add buttermilk, almond, vanilla and egg whites.
Then pour into 3 (8-inch) cake pans or 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Wash rice well.
Sprinkle over bottom of greased baking pan. Heat soup and milk together until smooth.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup over all.
Cover with foil and bake in a slow oven at 250° for 2 hours.

title: ginger rhubarb marmalade
directions: Add water to rhubarb and simmer until soft.
Measure 3 cups of this mixture into a large pan.
Add sugar and ginger and mix well. Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Certo.
Stir and cool slightly.
Put in warm, clean jars and skim foam from top.
Add hot paraffin at once.
Cool and allow to set.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs. Add and stir flour, salt, oatmeal, vanilla, baking soda, hot water and chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease a large skillet.
Heat and sprinkle a layer of meat in skillet; saute and let it brown slightly.
Drain.
Pour in 1/2 of the batter, then meat, next onion and finally pepper.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with 2 cups of corn flakes or crumbled Ritz crackers, soaked in 1/2 cup melted butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken pieces in beaten eggs seasoned with salt.
Marinate overnight.
Coat chicken with seasoned bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in margarine.
Arrange chicken in casserole in layers.
On each layer, put strips of cheese and mushrooms.
Add chicken broth enough to cover.
Cover casserole first half hour, remove and finish baking until broth is almost dissolved at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets and peel.
Heat vinegar, sugar and 2 cups water. Heat to boiling.
Add beets; bring to a boil.
Pack in clean jars and seal.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine sugar, peanuts, syrup and salt.
Microwave on High 6 to 9 minutes or until light brown, stirring well every 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; stir well. Microwave on High 1 to 3 minutes or until mixture reaches the hard crack stage, 300°, when tested.
Peanuts will be light brown and syrup will be very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes one pound.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Boil zucchini until tender; drain and place in casserole dish with lid.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Stir.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 300° for approximately 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F (165°C). Lightly grease a medium baking sheet. Cut a slit in each jalapeno pepper. Remove and discard seeds and pulp. In a medium bowl, mix sausage, baking mix, Cheddar cheese, crushed red pepper and garlic salt. Stuff jalapenos with the Monterey Jack cheese cubes. Shape sausage mixture around the jalapenos to form balls. Arrange jalapeno balls on the prepared baking sheet. Bake 25 minutes in the preheated oven until lightly browned.

title: alaskan mincemeat cake(350~ oven)
directions: In saucepan, combine water, sugar and mincemeat, broken into pieces.
Bring to rolling boil for 3 minutes; stir occasionally. Cool.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to cold mincemeat mixture.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Grease a tube pan (flour bottom only).
Spoon in batter and bake for 60 to 65 minutes, or until tests done.
Remove from oven.
Cool at least 1 hour before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, sugar and oil.
Mix 4 to 5 cups of flour in; place dough in greased bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Punch down.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: paula's cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cake can be layered in Bundt cake pan with 3/4 cup brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes or just plain without the brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
(Very low-fat.) Enjoy.
Yield:
One 10-inch cake.

title: oyster patties
directions: Beat eggs; add oysters, salt, pepper and the cup of rolled cracker crumbs.
Add more crumbs if necessary to make the right consistency to make patties.
Fry in butter until brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine 2/3 sour cream, mayo and dry taco seasoning; set aside.
Layer, ingredient by ingredient, in 13 x 9-inch oblong pan refried beans, ground beef, salsa, small package of Cheddar, 1/3 sour cream, mayo mixture, rest of cheese, tomato, pepper and scallions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas waldorf
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and water and stir well.
Add cranberry juice.
Chill until partially congealed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Add sugar to egg yolks and beat 15 minutes.
Combine egg yolks with egg whites and beat 2 minutes more.
Add flour gradually until well blended.
Add baking powder with 1 tsp. flour while beating mixture slowly.
Add vanilla and beat only 1 to 2 minutes more. Bake in large round 12- inch pan, lightly greased and floured at 350° for 45 - 50
minutes.
Do not open oven.
Do not use tube pan, it's not large enough for this batter.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Stir margarine, flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and chopped pecans together in a bowl.
Spread on a cookie sheet, making sure that edges are the same thickness as center.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool; then crumble.
Spread 1/2 of the crumb mixture into a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch covered pan.
Spoon 1/2 gallon of softened vanilla ice cream over nuts.
Spread 1 jar of caramel topping over ice cream.
Spread rest of crumbs over topping. Freeze!

title: strawberry-rhubarb cream pie
directions: Stir equal amounts of shortening and hot water until shortening is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 3 times as much flour as water.
Easier to mix and handle than other pie crusts.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 X 9 X 2 pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs and pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut, and nuts.
Press the ingredients firmly with a fork to pack.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.

title: cake dessert
directions: When cake is done, poke holes in cake.
Add crushed pineapple. Add topping of cream cheese and milk, whipped.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: pineapple coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Work in the softened margarine until well blended.
Mix the milk, eggs and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Mix by hand until well blended.
Pour 1/2 into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan or dish.
Mix the pie filling with lemon juice; spread on top of batter.
Spoon remaining batter over fruit; spread around carefully to cover.

title: julie's crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saut onion and celery in butter; add flour and blend.
Add milk and blend.
Remove from heat; add egg yolk, crabmeat, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip. Make chocolate pudding according to package directions, then fold into cream cheese mixture.
Beat Oreo cookies (do not remove cream inside) until cream and cookies are blended.
Use blender or food processor.
You can start to layer in a flowerpot.
Put foil around the pot so nothing falls out of bottom.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix thoroughly. Add flavoring.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan (grease and flour).

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add eggs and blend.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Dough will be soft.
Refrigerate until stiff.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix and roll into balls.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, green onions, lemon juice and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in eggs, mayo, pickle relish and mustard. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Scoop out center of tomatoes, leaving 1/4 to 1/2-inch head space.
Serve salad in tomato or on lettuce leaves.
Serves 4.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook noodles per package instructions.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add Ragu to meat.
Layer noodles, then hamburger mixture, cottage cheese and shredded cheeses.
Repeat layers again.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted or microwave in microwave-safe dish.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Spread crushed wafers
on
bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cream margarine and
sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Spread over wafers. Sprinkle nuts over egg mixture.
Spoon pineapple over nuts.
Whip cream
until
stiff.
Pour
over fruit in a smooth layer.
Cover with remaining crushed wafers.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Serves 15.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with vegetables.

title: play dough
directions: Getting ready:
Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in a medium pot.
Add water, food coloring and oil.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Spread rice in an 8 x 12-inch utility dish.
Layer fryer over rice.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion soup mix.
Top with whichever soup you choose and water.
Cover with plastic wrap. Place in center of oven.
Cook for 10 minutes on High and then 25 minutes on 75% power (or until chicken is done).
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: halibut quiche
directions: Prepare pastry for a 9-inch single crust pie and line a pie plate with it.
Place 1 cup flaked, precooked halibut in the prepared pie crust.
Shred the Swiss cheese and chop the onion, then sprinkle these over the halibut.
Beat eggs lightly and beat in half and half, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour the egg mixture over the ingredients in the pie plate.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce the oven temperature to 300° and continue baking for 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Remove from the oven and let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend thoroughly the flour, sugar, Crisco and salt.
In small bowl mix water, vinegar and egg. Pour over dry ingredients and mix. Makes 4 to 5 crusts. Can be frozen as large hamburger patty shape.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: In pan, put ingredients in layers, then salt and pepper.
Bake 2 hours at 375° or until done.

title: old fashioned pot roast with vegetables
directions: Rub roast with salt and pepper; spread with mustard and flour. Place in
roasting
pan and brown on top of stove with drippings; slice
onions,
turnips,
squash
and potatoes and place around roast.
Do
not
slice
too
small.
Season with salt, then
add tomatoes and bake covered for about 3 hours in a 350° oven.

title: donut muffin
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
You can also add chopped apples and raisins, etc.
Makes 9 muffins.
Put a little water in unfilled cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat until berries are soft, about 15 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a small skillet, saute onions and mushrooms in melted butter.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, chicken broth, parsley and salt.
Combine with cooked rice.
Add additional butter, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Cream oleo; add brown sugar, nuts and flour.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix blueberry filling, 1 cup powdered sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Spread over cream cheese mix.
Next spread Cool Whip over top and refrigerate until serving time.

title: jambalaya(makes 2 servings)
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add ham, pepper, onion, celery and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Add tomatoes, water, Worcestershire, curry powder and hot sauce; bring to boil.
Add rice and shrimp. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed.

title: phyllis' red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa and add to the mixture.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk and flavorings.
Alternately add soda and vinegar and don't beat hard, just blend.

title: taco chicken
directions: Moisten chicken.
Roll it in the mix.
Bake at 350° until done (30 to 40 minutes or more).
In the last 5 minutes cover with grated Cheddar cheese and melt.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Add zucchini and chopped nuts.
Pour into tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: terrific sweet potato casserole(this is a great holiday recipe.)
directions: Mix together well. Sprinkle over top of sweet potatoes. Bake at 400° until lightly brown (about 10 minutes). Turn down oven to 275° for about 30 minutes. Cooking time is about 40 minutes, total.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix together the broccoli, red onion, bacon and cheese.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let frozen bread dough rise in greased pan per package instructions.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Wash cucumbers; slice unpared cucumbers very thin.
Add onion, sliced equally as thin.
Mix all remaining ingredients in a bowl and stir until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over cucumbers and onion; toss gently.
If dressing is added too far in advance, then salad will become soggy.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and season with salt, pepper, onion, garlic (your choice of seasoning).
Drain the grease.
Peel potatoes, slice in cubes and cook.
When done make into mashed potatoes.
Put ground beef in a large flat casserole or lasagna pan.
Mix in tomato soup and green beans.
On top of mixture put mashed potatoes, you can scoop in sections or smooth over entire mixture.
Put in 350 degree oven and cook until the sauce is bubbling and hot.
Usually about 30 minutes.
